WEBVTT

00:51.342 --> 00:53.011
I swear to God, I didn't touch shit!

00:53.094 --> 00:55.764
So the gate just opened up all on its own,
like magic?

00:55.847 --> 00:57.807
It must've been some kind of malfunction.

00:57.891 --> 00:59.184
Let me get this straight.

00:59.267 --> 01:02.771
There was a malfunction
at the exact moment that truck showed up?

01:02.854 --> 01:04.564
You expect me to believe that, soldier?

01:04.647 --> 01:06.316
I swear. I don't know what happened.

01:06.399 --> 01:08.651
What if it was a malfunction?

01:09.569 --> 01:12.697
Only one not caused by us.

01:28.713 --> 01:30.840
All right, lab rats, let's scurry up.

01:30.924 --> 01:34.636
An entire dimension's about
to come crashing down on our heads.

01:37.305 --> 01:38.431
Hey.

01:39.557 --> 01:40.683
Is everything okay?

01:41.851 --> 01:42.769
Listen,

01:42.852 --> 01:46.106
I know this plan is totally mad,
and a million things have to go right,

01:46.189 --> 01:48.942
and a million things could
and probably will go wrong.

01:49.025 --> 01:52.112
But we can do this. I know it.

01:52.695 --> 01:56.074
One last fight,
and this whole nightmare, it'll be over.

01:56.658 --> 01:58.243
It'll finally be over.

02:31.651 --> 02:33.403
Well, hello there.

02:33.486 --> 02:35.613
MAC, this is Wolfpack. Do you copy--

02:35.697 --> 02:37.991
-What do you think you're doing?
-Alerting the Doc.

02:38.074 --> 02:39.993
That bitch has a God complex.

02:40.076 --> 02:41.870
All she'll do is slow us down.

02:42.453 --> 02:43.288
No.

02:43.913 --> 02:45.999
We're bagging this freak ourselves.

04:53.501 --> 04:56.546
-Do you think they're all right?
-The truck is faster than a Humvee.

04:56.629 --> 04:59.257
Let's be conservative,
say five miles faster.

04:59.340 --> 05:01.801
They had a six minute,
20 second head start,

05:01.884 --> 05:04.387
giving them an additional lead
of about half a mile.

05:04.470 --> 05:06.806
So they're fine for now,

05:06.889 --> 05:09.767
but the real shit hasn't started yet.

05:09.851 --> 05:11.686
Erica, language, please.

05:11.769 --> 05:15.940
This isn't Intro to Science.
This situation demands cussing.

05:19.694 --> 05:22.947
-So, how's it feel?
-What?

05:23.031 --> 05:26.451
Helping to save the world and all that.

05:27.327 --> 05:28.995
It feels pretty swell.

05:29.787 --> 05:31.748
Pretty goddamn swell.

05:44.469 --> 05:45.845
Go! Go! Go!

05:45.928 --> 05:48.222
Breach! Move, move, move!

06:16.793 --> 06:18.336
Hey, Robin, yeah.

06:18.419 --> 06:20.421
Can you please tell me that
that was you guys

06:20.505 --> 06:22.590
and not more of those, like, mutant Cujos?

06:23.383 --> 06:26.052
It's us, and it's too early
to be stressed, Vic. Save it for later.

06:26.135 --> 06:29.722
Yeah, no, copy that, yeah. No.
Bottling… Bottling emotions.

06:35.728 --> 06:39.565
No sign of an evil moving planet.

06:40.316 --> 06:43.111
Well, that's good.
'Cause this is gonna take some time.

06:43.694 --> 06:45.196
All right, we should split up.

06:45.822 --> 06:47.240
Use both ladders.

06:47.740 --> 06:49.951
Don't rush. Pace yourselves.

06:50.034 --> 06:53.830
There are platforms along the way,
so use them to rest.

06:53.913 --> 06:54.914
All right.

06:56.582 --> 06:57.875
Let's do this.

07:43.129 --> 07:44.130
You okay?

07:54.015 --> 07:55.683
Don't be frightened.

07:55.766 --> 07:57.268
These are all friends.

07:57.977 --> 07:59.562
They're just here to watch.

08:00.146 --> 08:01.814
Don't focus on them.

08:02.398 --> 08:03.858
Yes, Papa.

08:16.704 --> 08:20.958
And let there be light.

08:25.004 --> 08:27.673
All right, nice work, Bald Eagle.

08:27.757 --> 08:29.342
Now get up to the roof.

08:29.425 --> 08:31.302
Careful with that C-4.

08:31.886 --> 08:33.763
I don't wanna blow the Upside Down
with us in it.

08:34.514 --> 08:36.682
Oh, I was planning on carelessness.

08:36.766 --> 08:39.602
But you're right, Jim.
Caution here would be wise.

08:46.400 --> 08:47.276
All right.

08:48.569 --> 08:50.029
Now remember,

08:50.112 --> 08:53.908
two slow knocks means…

08:54.408 --> 08:57.328
-The Abyss started to move.
-That's right.

08:57.411 --> 09:01.332
And you and your sister get in position,
but you wait. You do not attack.

09:01.415 --> 09:04.460
The second I get confirmation
that planet's close enough to the tower,

09:04.544 --> 09:07.463
then I'm gonna give you three fast knocks.

09:07.547 --> 09:09.715
Then we strike. We kill Henry.

09:09.799 --> 09:15.513
And we, uh, pray to God Dustin's right,
and that planet stops moving.

09:16.722 --> 09:19.141
What could possibly go wrong, right?

09:21.227 --> 09:23.396
If something does go wrong,

09:24.188 --> 09:26.816
I need you to promise me
you won't pull me out.

09:27.817 --> 09:29.694
Not until I'm sure he's dead.

09:33.364 --> 09:34.282
Okay, well,

09:35.491 --> 09:37.743
then I'm gonna need a promise
from you too.

09:37.827 --> 09:41.080
If by some miracle this plan works,
we're getting the hell out of here.

09:41.163 --> 09:45.585
Doc Kay and her plans,
that's a problem for another day.

09:47.378 --> 09:48.421
Deal?

10:02.476 --> 10:03.978
Let's end this, kid.

11:16.425 --> 11:18.094
-You want some?
-Yeah.

11:30.022 --> 11:31.774
Hey, um…

11:32.775 --> 11:35.403
What you said earlier at the Squawk…

11:36.696 --> 11:37.780
I'm sorry.

11:38.489 --> 11:41.534
I mean, not sorry about what you said.
That came out wrong.

11:41.617 --> 11:43.744
Or not came out wrong. Jesus Christ.

11:43.828 --> 11:44.995
It's okay.

11:45.871 --> 11:47.373
No, it's… it's not.

11:47.456 --> 11:50.793
I should have been there for you,
and I wasn't.

11:50.876 --> 11:54.755
And I guess I was just so self-absorbed
that I couldn't see it.

11:54.839 --> 11:57.550
I just… I feel like an idiot, and I…

11:58.759 --> 11:59.635
I'm sorry.

12:00.219 --> 12:04.056
You don't have to be sorry.
And you are not an idiot. You're not.

12:04.140 --> 12:05.266
It's just…

12:06.350 --> 12:10.396
I didn't even understand it myself
for the longest time.

12:11.939 --> 12:15.067
I just… I think it needed to happen
the way it happened.

12:15.151 --> 12:16.610
I needed to find my own way.

12:17.319 --> 12:19.905
But what matters is
that you're still here,

12:19.989 --> 12:22.491
and you still think we can be friends.

12:23.075 --> 12:24.827
Friends? No, thanks.

12:26.120 --> 12:27.288
Best friends.

12:29.874 --> 12:31.375
All right, come on.

12:33.502 --> 12:34.670
We've got a planet to catch.

12:37.506 --> 12:39.383
What the hell is taking them so long?

12:39.467 --> 12:43.262
I don't know. Maybe it has something to do
with the fact that it's a 500-foot tower.

12:44.013 --> 12:45.848
If something's wrong, they'll contact us.

12:45.931 --> 12:48.559
Yeah, no, yeah.
I mean, unless they're already dead.

12:50.394 --> 12:53.647
Okay, uh, stress gives me
the munchies, so I, um…

12:55.149 --> 12:56.400
Do you want anything?

12:56.484 --> 12:57.526
No.

12:57.610 --> 12:58.569
Okay.

12:59.820 --> 13:00.863
Actually, can I get a--

13:03.240 --> 13:04.241
Vickie?

13:06.035 --> 13:07.077
Vickie!

13:34.021 --> 13:35.189
Holy shit.

14:01.966 --> 14:05.678
Mm. I swear to God,
nothing cures anxiety quite like a bowl--

14:37.293 --> 14:38.627
Trippy, isn't it?

14:42.298 --> 14:43.173
Hi.

14:57.897 --> 14:59.023
Thanks, man.

14:59.565 --> 15:00.733
Okay.

15:11.702 --> 15:13.495
It's pretty damn spectacular.

15:15.080 --> 15:17.166
It's almost too bad
we have to blow it all up.

15:30.679 --> 15:32.389
Mother of God.

15:49.990 --> 15:52.576
Jim, do you, uh, copy?

15:52.660 --> 15:54.119
Yeah, yeah, copy.

15:54.203 --> 15:56.413
Well, I got some good news, bad news.

15:56.497 --> 15:58.499
Uh, good news is our theory was correct.

15:58.582 --> 16:01.251
A giant planet is descending
upon our heads.

16:01.335 --> 16:04.046
The bad news is our theory was correct.

16:04.129 --> 16:07.132
A giant planet is descending
upon our heads.

16:07.216 --> 16:09.259
-How long do we have?
-Not long.

16:09.343 --> 16:11.553
Supergirl better be close in there.

16:17.643 --> 16:18.978
Come on, El.

16:35.244 --> 16:38.414
So this is Vecna, right now in the Abyss?

16:39.456 --> 16:41.792
You don't have to whisper, but yes.

16:42.459 --> 16:45.796
Okay, so why don't we just kill him
right here?

16:45.879 --> 16:47.631
I mean, he seems pretty damn vulnerable.

16:47.715 --> 16:48.799
We can't hurt him here.

16:48.882 --> 16:50.259
We have to enter his mind.

16:50.342 --> 16:51.760
-Isn't this his mind?
-No.

16:51.844 --> 16:53.262
-It's my mind.
-What?

16:53.345 --> 16:54.221
Hold on.

17:07.192 --> 17:08.318
Are you okay?

17:11.155 --> 17:12.448
Oh, great.

17:13.032 --> 17:15.075
I've really missed this.

17:15.826 --> 17:16.702
Hop.

17:18.662 --> 17:20.080
The Abyss is moving.

17:20.164 --> 17:22.499
-How close are we to Henry's house?
-Not close.

17:22.583 --> 17:24.543
-How not close?
-I'm not sure.

17:24.626 --> 17:26.420
You said you know his mind
backwards and forwards.

17:26.503 --> 17:29.423
Yeah, I do, but there are a shit ton
of memories in here.

17:29.506 --> 17:32.634
We're like Dorothy in Oz,
except there's no Yellow Brick Road.

17:32.718 --> 17:35.471
Everything connects,
but there are long ways and short ways.

17:35.554 --> 17:37.765
-Well, we need a short way.
-Yeah, no shit.

17:37.848 --> 17:40.267
Now can you just stop talking
while I try and think?

17:40.350 --> 17:43.687
-Joyce, this that stupid play of yours?
-Better see you there, Harrington.

17:43.771 --> 17:46.106
Yeah, on a Friday night? You wish.

17:46.190 --> 17:47.941
Come on, I have an idea.

17:48.025 --> 17:49.610
-Is that Joyce?
-Yep.

17:49.693 --> 17:51.820
And through that door,
Hop's sneaking a joint.

17:51.904 --> 17:54.782
And that way, Mr. Wheeler
is feeling up Mrs. Wheeler.

17:54.865 --> 17:57.826
I wish we had time to sightsee,
but we've got a play to catch.

18:14.343 --> 18:16.220
Three, two, one, go!

18:17.471 --> 18:19.306
Yeah, we're gonna sweep around the back.

18:25.104 --> 18:26.313
West room's clear.

18:33.362 --> 18:34.905
South side!

18:39.409 --> 18:42.329
We are at location. Negative on…

19:06.937 --> 19:09.481
No, no, no, guys. It's not lining up.

19:09.565 --> 19:10.941
What do you mean?

19:11.024 --> 19:13.527
Look. The tower needle,
it's not lining up with the rift.

19:14.361 --> 19:15.404
Shit.

19:15.487 --> 19:17.531
-If the Abyss hits the needle…
-This tower's going down.

19:18.157 --> 19:20.284
That's great. That's just great.

19:20.951 --> 19:23.412
Hey, Chief,
we're gonna need El to stop this planet.

19:23.495 --> 19:26.373
-On the sooner side, please.
-How soon?

19:26.957 --> 19:28.000
Thirty seconds?

19:53.150 --> 19:54.818
What are we doing?

19:54.902 --> 19:56.361
-Waiting.
-For what?

19:58.780 --> 20:00.782
Three. We need to strike.

20:03.869 --> 20:06.079
Chief, talk to me.
What's going on in there?

20:06.163 --> 20:08.665
I don't know. I can't talk to her.
I gave her the signal.

20:08.749 --> 20:10.417
Well, nothing's happening over here,

20:10.500 --> 20:14.087
and we're about to be squashed
by a moving planet. So give it again!

20:15.589 --> 20:18.342
-We have to go.
-This is the only way. Just trust me.

20:29.144 --> 20:30.229
Shit!

20:54.795 --> 20:56.171
Look out! Look out! Look out!

20:58.465 --> 20:59.967
Now!

21:11.895 --> 21:12.896
Steve!

21:18.110 --> 21:19.987
Steve!

21:38.547 --> 21:42.009
Just hold on! I got you. Just hold on!

21:52.227 --> 21:54.438
We're alive! We're alive!

21:54.521 --> 21:56.440
Shit, I thought you were toast.

21:58.567 --> 22:03.822
The Abyss stopped! El got him!
I repeat, El got the bastard!

22:04.406 --> 22:06.825
Yes! Wow! Come on!

22:09.786 --> 22:13.081
You came back. You came back for me.

22:13.165 --> 22:16.501
And I'm not leaving your side, ever again.

22:16.585 --> 22:18.879
Not until we're out of here. All of us.

22:18.962 --> 22:20.255
It's her! It's the monster!

22:20.339 --> 22:23.008
-Get up!
-No, I'm not the monster.

22:23.091 --> 22:24.051
And I can prove it.

22:54.498 --> 22:55.374
All clear!

22:55.457 --> 22:56.333
Hold this.

22:57.542 --> 22:58.627
-Hey!
-Easy!

22:58.710 --> 22:59.878
-You ready?
-Ready?

22:59.961 --> 23:00.837
Yeah.

23:01.630 --> 23:04.466
Okay, easy. Easy. I got you, man.

23:04.549 --> 23:06.218
All right, here goes nothing.

23:26.154 --> 23:27.823
Holy shit.

23:28.657 --> 23:30.867
Does this officially make us
space travelers?

23:30.951 --> 23:33.370
Interdimensional space travelers.

23:34.079 --> 23:36.164
Suck it, Armstrong.

24:00.814 --> 24:02.232
It's over.

24:06.111 --> 24:07.404
Where are they?

24:07.487 --> 24:09.281
With Max.

24:10.073 --> 24:11.116
Safe.

24:14.995 --> 24:16.872
Where are they?

24:17.456 --> 24:18.457
I told you.

24:19.082 --> 24:20.292
With Max.

24:21.209 --> 24:23.128
Far away from here.

24:24.713 --> 24:26.506
You can't believe it, can you?

24:27.632 --> 24:30.135
That they would ever
see through your lies.

24:32.179 --> 24:33.430
Why can't he see us?

24:33.513 --> 24:36.808
Because Mr. Whatsit isn't the only one
with magic powers.

24:42.147 --> 24:43.857
That's why you take children.

24:44.608 --> 24:48.945
Because you think they have weak minds.

24:53.408 --> 24:56.161
But they're smarter than you think.

24:57.496 --> 24:58.538
And you?

24:59.539 --> 25:01.166
Are you smart?

25:02.501 --> 25:04.586
You let yourself get caught.

25:07.506 --> 25:09.257
And in here…

25:11.051 --> 25:15.597
I will find all the answers I need.

25:31.446 --> 25:33.073
Holy shit.

25:33.156 --> 25:35.617
It's him. He's the Black Thing.

25:36.201 --> 25:40.288
Everything Holly told you is true.
He is trying to destroy our world.

25:40.372 --> 25:42.958
But he can't do it, not without you.

25:43.041 --> 25:45.919
We have to escape. Right now.

25:53.176 --> 25:54.970
Stronger, aren't we?

25:57.556 --> 25:58.848
So am I.

26:00.225 --> 26:01.101
Holly!

26:04.563 --> 26:06.147
I can follow her into his mind.

26:07.107 --> 26:10.110
We can end our brother, together.

26:22.789 --> 26:23.999
Come on!

26:28.461 --> 26:29.754
Now!

26:30.880 --> 26:31.965
Hello, brother.

26:55.822 --> 26:57.365
Don't know about you guys,

26:58.158 --> 27:00.452
but I was expecting more like…

27:00.535 --> 27:02.704
-Deadly vines?
-Or monsters?

27:02.787 --> 27:05.707
I assume the hive mind works here too.
So if Henry died,

27:05.790 --> 27:08.126
-so did all his nasty, little minions.
-"If"?

27:08.209 --> 27:10.795
We don't know what's going on in the mind.

27:10.879 --> 27:12.964
I know El broke the spell
and stopped the Abyss,

27:13.048 --> 27:15.008
but she could still be fighting him.

27:16.760 --> 27:19.220
Hey. She's been training for this.

27:19.304 --> 27:22.682
And she's not alone.
She's got Kali and Max.

27:22.766 --> 27:26.227
And I'm sure Henry's dead.
And if he's not, he will be.

27:27.604 --> 27:28.605
Yeah.

27:30.440 --> 27:32.150
Great job keeping the morale up.

27:35.070 --> 27:36.071
Hey, man.

27:37.697 --> 27:38.657
Hey.

27:40.700 --> 27:42.661
Thought I was a goner back there.

27:44.663 --> 27:45.914
Owe you one.

27:46.623 --> 27:47.749
Yeah.

27:50.960 --> 27:53.088
Look, just because I don't like you,

27:53.963 --> 27:55.674
doesn't mean I want you dead.

27:57.342 --> 28:00.053
And I've got a feeling
we're gonna need you up here.

28:02.138 --> 28:04.432
I don't blame you, by the way.

28:05.141 --> 28:06.851
For not liking me.

28:06.935 --> 28:10.438
You know, I can be a real prick sometimes.

28:12.273 --> 28:13.274
Yeah.

28:13.942 --> 28:16.069
I mean, same.

28:19.614 --> 28:21.116
Look, Steve,

28:22.534 --> 28:24.327
when I was away in California,

28:25.870 --> 28:28.873
you were there for Nancy
when I couldn't be.

28:30.709 --> 28:35.714
And I thought that, you know,
that was why things were off with us.

28:37.549 --> 28:38.883
But the truth is

28:39.926 --> 28:42.053
our problems had nothing to do with you.

28:43.722 --> 28:46.391
It just took me a long time
to figure that out.

28:49.352 --> 28:50.353
And…

28:51.229 --> 28:52.522
to let her go.

28:57.152 --> 28:58.820
If we hadn't been so busy fighting,

28:58.903 --> 29:02.449
I probably could've saved you
a little bit of time, because…

29:03.450 --> 29:08.079
I've known for a while now me and Nance
were never really in the cards.

29:09.289 --> 29:12.208
You know, she's independent.
She's gotta get out there, and…

29:12.292 --> 29:14.753
-I don't know. I want…
-Six little nuggets?

29:17.005 --> 29:18.089
She told you that?

29:21.384 --> 29:23.178
You think it would've been better
if I'd said four?

29:24.304 --> 29:26.890
Maybe just not calling them nuggets.

29:26.973 --> 29:27.974
Right.

29:28.933 --> 29:31.311
Listen, bottom line, end of the day, I…

29:32.103 --> 29:34.689
I'd rather have her as a friend
than nothing at all.

29:35.648 --> 29:37.901
You know, she's… she's just really…

29:37.984 --> 29:39.194
-Special.
-Yeah.

29:41.654 --> 29:43.364
I guess we can agree on one thing.

29:44.532 --> 29:46.034
Yeah, I guess so.

29:49.913 --> 29:53.291
-I still don't like you, though.
-I wouldn't want it any other way.

29:55.585 --> 29:56.795
Hey, lovebirds!

29:56.878 --> 29:58.463
You're gonna wanna check this out.

30:01.049 --> 30:03.259
Jesus Christ.

30:12.977 --> 30:13.978
That's it.

30:14.646 --> 30:16.523
That's what I saw in my vision.

30:17.649 --> 30:18.983
The kids are in there.

30:20.944 --> 30:22.612
Then what are we waiting for?

30:32.455 --> 30:34.999
Derek? No! Derek, you have to keep going.

30:35.083 --> 30:37.335
-I can't.
-Derek, what are you doing? Come on!

30:37.418 --> 30:40.380
Just leave me!
Save yourselves, you dumbasses!

30:40.463 --> 30:41.506
No, don't be an idiot!

30:41.589 --> 30:44.425
-I'm not being an idiot!
-Yes, you are! No, you can't--

30:52.600 --> 30:54.519
-Is everyone okay?
-Yeah, we're okay.

30:54.602 --> 30:57.021
-Did you find him? Tell me you found him.
-He just vanished.

30:57.814 --> 30:59.274
He went back to the real world.

30:59.357 --> 31:01.401
He can come back. Will come back.

31:01.484 --> 31:02.735
How far to the cave?

31:02.819 --> 31:04.279
It's not far. Come on.

31:04.863 --> 31:06.489
Derek, we gotta go. Right now.

31:06.573 --> 31:07.699
Go! Run!

31:12.954 --> 31:16.791
Dustin! Lucas!
What's going on? Come on, talk to me!

32:20.688 --> 32:22.899
You knew this would happen.

32:24.734 --> 32:28.529
Just like you know
what will happen to her.

32:30.156 --> 32:31.866
Don't you see, Jane?

32:32.492 --> 32:37.372
It's a cycle.
It's a terrible, vicious cycle.

32:37.455 --> 32:40.291
But we can stop it. Tonight.

32:44.295 --> 32:45.463
How?

32:46.047 --> 32:49.801
After we kill our brother,
after the children are rescued,

32:49.884 --> 32:53.805
we don't leave with the others.
We stay on the bridge.

32:53.888 --> 32:56.015
When the Upside Down vanishes…

32:59.102 --> 33:00.061
so will we.

33:02.647 --> 33:04.148
It is the only way, Jane.

33:05.274 --> 33:07.276
The only way.

33:08.528 --> 33:13.157
She's going to do it, Jim.
She's going to end her life.

33:13.241 --> 33:14.742
Show yourself!

33:15.785 --> 33:18.246
Show yourself, you lying bastard!

33:18.329 --> 33:23.710
I am many things, but I am not a liar.

33:23.793 --> 33:26.504
I have seen into her mind,

33:26.587 --> 33:29.966
and now I have seen into yours.

33:30.049 --> 33:32.218
What rage it holds!

33:32.802 --> 33:37.348
One daughter dead because of you,
and soon another.

33:37.432 --> 33:38.725
Show yourself!

33:38.808 --> 33:42.937
You are as you fear.

33:43.021 --> 33:45.732
You are the curse.

34:04.292 --> 34:05.293
No!

34:21.726 --> 34:22.935
Why's he signaling?

34:27.273 --> 34:29.525
-That's not a signal.
-Then what is it?

34:39.660 --> 34:40.620
Oh, God.

34:41.913 --> 34:43.122
Holly!

34:43.748 --> 34:45.124
Get to the cave!

34:48.252 --> 34:50.421
I got you. Hang on.

34:51.005 --> 34:51.964
Hang on!

34:54.425 --> 34:56.511
Hold on. Hold on.

35:03.309 --> 35:04.811
What did you do?

35:13.778 --> 35:14.904
Hi there.

35:29.335 --> 35:30.253
Hey, Doc.

35:30.962 --> 35:32.755
Kids left out their homework.

35:43.933 --> 35:45.726
-Max!
-What happened?

35:45.810 --> 35:48.271
She just poofed away like a goddamn ghost!

35:48.354 --> 35:50.940
Was it the Black Thing?
Did the Black Thing take them?

35:51.023 --> 35:52.233
Listen up!

35:52.316 --> 35:56.988
We keep to the plan. Get to the cave.
The Black Thing can't hurt us there.

35:57.071 --> 36:00.825
So follow me, keep quiet, and stay close.

36:00.908 --> 36:02.785
-Let's go! Come on.
-Come on, guys.

36:02.869 --> 36:04.412
Let's go! Hurry!

36:04.996 --> 36:07.999
The kids are all alone in there.
You have to get us back to them.

36:08.082 --> 36:12.003
I can't, not without the bath.
He locked us out.

36:12.086 --> 36:15.464
We have to get to the Abyss,
join the others. We can kill him there.

36:15.548 --> 36:19.260
There is no time. The worlds will collide
long before we reach him.

36:19.343 --> 36:22.013
Not if Holly and the kids make it
to the cave.

36:22.096 --> 36:26.184
If Dustin is right,
without the kids, Henry can't do anything.

36:26.267 --> 36:27.852
That's a lot of ifs.

36:28.561 --> 36:29.604
What do you wanna do?

36:31.439 --> 36:32.982
We can't give up, not now.

36:33.065 --> 36:35.651
Isn't that exactly what you're doing?
Giving up.

36:37.820 --> 36:39.322
I know the truth.

36:41.073 --> 36:42.617
Henry showed me your plan.

36:42.700 --> 36:44.285
Henry lied to you.

36:44.368 --> 36:45.828
He tricked you.

36:45.912 --> 36:48.581
He used you, and you fell for it.

36:48.664 --> 36:50.333
Then look me in the eye and tell me.

36:51.375 --> 36:52.793
Tell me.

36:52.877 --> 36:55.338
Tell me you don't plan
on killing yourself tonight.

36:57.048 --> 36:59.050
We don't have time for this.
We have to go.

36:59.133 --> 37:00.927
I won't detonate it.

37:03.179 --> 37:05.139
-I won't.
-What?

37:05.223 --> 37:06.933
I will not detonate the C-4,

37:07.016 --> 37:11.062
not until I know that you are safe
with the others back in Hawkins.

37:11.145 --> 37:16.192
If we kill Henry and don't destroy
the Upside Down, nothing matters.

37:16.275 --> 37:21.280
Which is why I will destroy it
once I know that you're safe.

37:21.364 --> 37:22.615
Why are you doing this?

37:22.698 --> 37:25.243
Because Henry's gotten to him,
and he's lost his mind.

37:25.326 --> 37:28.120
-Kali, wait.
-No. This is bigger than him, Jane.

37:28.829 --> 37:32.166
-Bigger than any of us.
-Yeah, go ahead. Go ahead. Shoot me.

37:32.250 --> 37:35.336
If I'm alive, then so is Henry.

37:36.045 --> 37:37.755
I have to end the cycle.

37:37.838 --> 37:40.758
You will. You will. But not like this.

37:40.841 --> 37:43.844
Not with more violence.
Not with more pain.

37:45.054 --> 37:47.306
There's already been so much pain.

37:47.890 --> 37:49.475
From the moment you were born.

37:49.976 --> 37:53.688
Your mother was taken from you.
Your childhood was taken from you.

37:53.771 --> 37:58.276
You've been attacked, manipulated, abused

37:59.568 --> 38:01.070
by terrible people.

38:01.153 --> 38:04.323
Life has been so unfair to you,

38:05.116 --> 38:06.284
so cruel.

38:08.119 --> 38:09.537
But you never let it break you.

38:09.620 --> 38:11.580
And I need you to fight, kid.

38:12.581 --> 38:15.167
I just need you to fight one last time.

38:16.002 --> 38:18.629
Fight for the happy days
on the other side of this.

38:18.713 --> 38:20.006
Fight for…

38:21.549 --> 38:24.385
for a world beyond Hawkins.

38:25.094 --> 38:27.722
Fight for that day
that you have a kid of your own,

38:28.889 --> 38:31.642
and you give her the life
that you never had.

38:35.146 --> 38:37.815
For the day you get so angry
because she invites some boy over,

38:37.898 --> 38:39.900
and she won't keep the door open
three inches.

38:41.527 --> 38:42.778
I know.

38:42.862 --> 38:45.364
I know you don't believe
you can have any of this.

38:45.865 --> 38:47.325
But I promise you

38:48.034 --> 38:50.244
we will find a way to make it real.

38:50.911 --> 38:53.914
You will find a way to make it real.

38:55.249 --> 38:56.584
Because you have to.

38:59.503 --> 39:01.130
Because you deserve it.

39:05.801 --> 39:06.635
Jim!

39:06.719 --> 39:08.304
Jim! Are you there, Jim?

39:08.387 --> 39:12.725
I don't want to add to the stress,
but we've got company.

39:33.621 --> 39:36.248
Come on! Come on!
We're almost there! Keep going!

39:36.332 --> 39:39.293
Through this gap right here! Right here!
Come on! One by one!

39:39.377 --> 39:40.586
Go! Go! Go!

39:42.671 --> 39:43.589
Debbie, wait!

39:46.634 --> 39:47.676
Have you seen Derek?

39:49.720 --> 39:51.514
-Derek!
-Wait! Holly!

39:51.597 --> 39:53.432
-Derek!
-Holly!

40:01.816 --> 40:04.902
Come on! Come on! We got this!
We gotta go! Come on! Hurry up!

40:04.985 --> 40:08.906
Keep running! Come on, Derek! Come on!

40:08.989 --> 40:11.784
Get inside. He's coming! Go!

40:11.867 --> 40:12.868
Come on!

40:17.748 --> 40:18.833
Holly!

40:26.715 --> 40:27.633
Go!

40:29.927 --> 40:31.929
-Suck my fat one!
-Come on!

40:36.392 --> 40:37.476
Holly!

40:39.145 --> 40:41.105
-Are you okay?
-We're okay. We're okay.

40:41.188 --> 40:42.481
Was it him? Was it Henry?

40:42.565 --> 40:47.695
Yes, but he can't get us. Okay?
Not in here. We're safe now.

40:47.778 --> 40:49.321
-Okay.
-We're safe.

41:12.887 --> 41:15.055
-Why are you staring at me?
-I'm not!

41:18.225 --> 41:21.520
We're just getting really close, okay?
And we don't know what's in there,

41:21.604 --> 41:24.315
so I think you should be sharing
some of that firepower.

41:24.398 --> 41:25.733
You have firepower.

41:25.816 --> 41:27.568
Three Molotovs? Come on!

41:27.651 --> 41:29.653
Unless you're okay living
with the guilt of my death,

41:29.737 --> 41:31.572
I'm gonna need one of those goddamn guns!

41:39.788 --> 41:40.831
Holy shit!

41:41.457 --> 41:42.458
Thanks!

41:45.127 --> 41:46.420
Those are flares.

41:46.504 --> 41:47.505
What?

41:48.547 --> 41:51.217
Flares. She gave you a flare gun, dude.

41:52.718 --> 41:53.844
What?

41:53.928 --> 41:55.054
Flare gun?

41:55.137 --> 41:58.557
Nancy! Nancy, what the hell is this?
Are you serious?

41:59.600 --> 42:00.976
You think this is a joke?

42:02.728 --> 42:04.563
What the hell am I gonna do
with a flare gun?

42:08.359 --> 42:10.110
Hey! Will!

42:11.570 --> 42:12.488
-Will!
-Will!

42:12.571 --> 42:15.366
Hey! What is it? What's wrong?

42:15.449 --> 42:16.450
It's Henry.

42:17.910 --> 42:18.786
He's alive.

42:51.610 --> 42:53.195
Resist it.

42:55.531 --> 42:57.366
How did you find me?

43:04.540 --> 43:06.000
They sent you.

43:08.002 --> 43:09.420
Resist it.

43:17.553 --> 43:19.221
Will!

43:22.141 --> 43:23.142
What was that?

43:23.726 --> 43:24.727
Holly?

43:26.437 --> 43:27.354
Stay here.

43:47.374 --> 43:49.460
What's going on? What do you see?

43:50.210 --> 43:53.631
It's Henry. He's made it into the cave.

43:53.714 --> 43:59.094
He's coming! Go! Go! Up here! Everyone!
Come on! Go, go, go, go, go!

44:00.346 --> 44:04.099
Hurry! Come on, quickly! Go! Go!

44:04.183 --> 44:07.936
He's found them.
He's found Holly and the kids.

44:08.020 --> 44:09.271
Okay, what about El?

44:09.355 --> 44:12.483
Do you see El? Or Kali? Or Max?

44:12.566 --> 44:15.277
They're alone. They're all alone.

44:17.655 --> 44:19.865
-Go! Go! Hurry!
-Come on, guys!

44:27.414 --> 44:30.459
Could you stop him? With your powers?

44:30.542 --> 44:33.128
I can try. Just keep going.

44:33.712 --> 44:34.838
Go! Go!

44:46.225 --> 44:47.810
Move! Move! Move!

45:00.781 --> 45:01.824
Come on! Come on!

45:23.929 --> 45:25.097
Oh, God.

45:40.237 --> 45:41.780
Hurry! Let's go!

45:41.864 --> 45:44.616
Quickly! Come on!
It's right up here, this hole!

45:44.700 --> 45:48.787
Joshua, down there! Be careful, okay?
Keep moving! Thomas, you next!

46:00.799 --> 46:02.301
Jim, do you copy?

46:02.801 --> 46:04.803
Jim, do you copy?

46:05.471 --> 46:06.764
Goddammit!

46:23.322 --> 46:24.156
Kali.

46:31.455 --> 46:35.459
Well, well. Look what we got here.

46:36.627 --> 46:38.712
Your friends just left you here, huh?

46:38.796 --> 46:40.547
Well, that's not very nice, now is it?

46:44.384 --> 46:45.344
Hmm.

46:46.136 --> 46:47.596
Get her out of here.

47:01.276 --> 47:02.444
Hey. Hey.

47:03.028 --> 47:05.280
I got you. I got you.

47:06.156 --> 47:07.908
And I got you.

47:13.664 --> 47:16.667
All right, listen.
Anything you see in here is not real.

47:16.750 --> 47:19.378
It can't hurt you.
Just keep your eyes on me, okay?

47:19.461 --> 47:20.337
-Okay.
-Okay.

47:23.674 --> 47:24.550
Come on, let's go.

47:26.927 --> 47:28.220
Keep going. Stay close.

47:28.303 --> 47:30.347
Eyes on me, okay? Eyes on me.

47:30.430 --> 47:31.682
Just keep moving.

47:33.100 --> 47:34.434
Holy shitballs!

47:34.518 --> 47:36.436
Eyes on me, Derek!

47:39.064 --> 47:42.067
Through here. You get to the other side,
and you wait for me.

47:42.150 --> 47:43.694
Debbie, you first.

47:48.115 --> 47:49.366
Thomas, your turn.

47:49.449 --> 47:51.410
-Come on, guys. Let's hurry up!
-Let's go!

47:51.493 --> 47:54.329
-Come on! Come on! We got this.
-Hurry up, Glenn.

47:57.291 --> 47:58.292
Go!

48:04.423 --> 48:08.635
Tell me where the other freak is,
or this one dies right here, right now.

48:08.719 --> 48:11.680
I don't know what you're talking about.
It's just us.

48:12.931 --> 48:15.893
You think I'm playing a game here?
Where is she?

48:28.196 --> 48:32.284
Okay. Oh, what are you doing, Murray?
This is not a good plan.

48:33.452 --> 48:34.745
This is crazy.

48:34.828 --> 48:38.832
Okay. Here goes absolutely nothing.

48:40.250 --> 48:41.835
One last chance.

48:42.628 --> 48:44.338
Where is she?

48:54.097 --> 48:55.182
Go to hell.

48:56.475 --> 48:57.351
Okay, then.

50:24.396 --> 50:25.313
Kali.

50:25.981 --> 50:28.525
No, no, no!

50:28.608 --> 50:29.860
Kali. Kali.

50:29.943 --> 50:33.030
-Get bandages please.
-Keep pressure on the wound.

50:33.864 --> 50:35.365
Kali, look at me. Look at me.

50:35.449 --> 50:38.452
Hang in there, okay?
I'm here. It's gonna be okay.

50:39.536 --> 50:42.205
I'm not going to make it.

50:42.289 --> 50:46.835
No, don't say that. You will. You will.
You will make it, okay?

50:46.918 --> 50:48.170
Don't cry, Jane.

50:50.672 --> 50:51.673
My story…

50:52.632 --> 50:54.843
was always going to end here.

50:55.761 --> 50:56.762
No.

50:57.971 --> 50:59.306
No, no.

51:37.302 --> 51:38.220
Holly.

51:41.723 --> 51:42.724
Holly?

52:02.661 --> 52:04.371
How did you find me?

52:05.330 --> 52:06.581
Please.

52:07.332 --> 52:10.293
Please, mister. Don't shoot.

52:11.044 --> 52:12.129
Who are you?

52:12.838 --> 52:16.633
Henry. Henry Creel. I live near here.

52:16.716 --> 52:18.009
Who sent you?

52:18.093 --> 52:21.263
Nobody sent me.
I was in the caves. I heard a scream.

52:21.346 --> 52:24.349
They sent you. They sent you!

52:24.432 --> 52:26.935
You're just confused. You need a doctor.

52:32.232 --> 52:33.400
What's happening?

52:34.985 --> 52:37.070
He's in a memory now.

52:37.154 --> 52:39.030
And he's scared.

52:39.114 --> 52:41.032
He's so scared.

52:51.418 --> 52:54.171
Oh my God. Thank God. Thank God.
Thank God. Thank God.

52:54.254 --> 52:58.550
I thought you two were goners
for a minute there.

52:58.633 --> 52:59.926
Oh, what?

53:00.010 --> 53:02.804
No hug from the big man, huh?

53:02.888 --> 53:05.432
How about a "thank you
for destroying the Huey, Murray."

53:05.515 --> 53:08.602
"That was very brave and… and…"

53:10.187 --> 53:11.271
What's wrong?

53:12.105 --> 53:13.273
Wait.

53:13.356 --> 53:15.442
Kali. Where's… Where's Kali?

53:18.236 --> 53:19.404
Oh God.

53:20.363 --> 53:21.364
El, I'm…

53:22.991 --> 53:24.117
I'm so sorry.

53:42.302 --> 53:43.720
I can jump.

53:45.347 --> 53:47.515
I can jump those boulders to the Abyss.

53:48.016 --> 53:51.144
I'll be right there,
right at the tree. Shortcut.

53:52.312 --> 53:53.772
Henry's still up there.

53:53.855 --> 53:55.607
-If you fall…
-I won't.

53:55.690 --> 53:57.108
If you make it…

54:00.528 --> 54:01.947
I kill him.

54:02.030 --> 54:03.281
Oh, yeah?

54:03.907 --> 54:04.950
And then what?

54:14.751 --> 54:18.129
When I was a kid,
and you found me in the woods…

54:23.593 --> 54:24.803
I was scared.

54:26.388 --> 54:27.389
Really scared.

54:30.934 --> 54:32.727
I didn't understand the world.

54:33.687 --> 54:36.690
I didn't understand… people.

54:40.902 --> 54:42.279
You took me in.

54:47.242 --> 54:48.285
Raised me.

54:48.994 --> 54:49.995
Protected me.

54:50.537 --> 54:51.538
Mm.

55:06.761 --> 55:08.430
You became my dad.

55:17.188 --> 55:20.191
But I'm not… a kid anymore.

55:33.371 --> 55:34.748
And I'm not Sara.

55:45.091 --> 55:47.093
She didn't have a choice to make.

55:52.390 --> 55:53.391
But I do.

55:56.478 --> 55:57.645
And I need you

55:58.313 --> 56:00.607
to trust me to make the right choice.

56:08.073 --> 56:10.992
I need you to believe in me.

57:48.715 --> 57:51.551
Find me.

57:51.634 --> 57:54.596
Find me.

58:02.812 --> 58:05.273
Ah!

58:05.356 --> 58:10.403
You must resist it.

58:11.279 --> 58:14.574
It will consume you.

58:14.657 --> 58:19.621
It will consume all.

58:49.067 --> 58:50.443
It wasn't you.

58:52.153 --> 58:53.863
It was never you.

58:56.366 --> 58:57.909
Leave me alone.

58:57.992 --> 59:01.412
That's why the Mind Flayer didn't want you
in the cave.

59:01.496 --> 59:02.914
It didn't want you to remember.

59:06.626 --> 59:08.253
I said leave me alone.

59:08.336 --> 59:12.048
You were just a kid, a kid like me.

59:12.882 --> 59:14.509
And it used you.

59:15.176 --> 59:17.595
It used you to bring it here.

59:18.346 --> 59:20.223
You're just like me, Henry.

59:21.140 --> 59:22.392
A vessel.

59:23.476 --> 59:26.688
But you can resist it. Help us fight it.

59:26.771 --> 59:30.525
Don't let it win, Henry, please.
Don't let it win.

59:35.989 --> 59:36.948
No.

59:39.367 --> 59:40.994
It showed me the truth.

59:45.999 --> 59:50.128
It showed me that this world is broken.

59:50.211 --> 59:52.505
That man is broken.

59:52.589 --> 59:56.259
Don't listen to it, Henry.
It is controlling you right now.

1:00:05.101 --> 1:00:08.062
It has never controlled me.

1:00:09.272 --> 1:00:11.357
And I never controlled it.

1:00:22.702 --> 1:00:25.538
Don't you see, William?

1:00:26.247 --> 1:00:28.958
I could have resisted it.

1:00:29.876 --> 1:00:31.919
But I chose

1:00:32.879 --> 1:00:33.963
to join it.

1:00:40.261 --> 1:00:41.304
Oh my God.

1:00:53.066 --> 1:00:55.777
It needs… me.

1:01:01.658 --> 1:01:03.284
And I need it.

1:01:10.833 --> 1:01:11.793
We…

1:01:15.463 --> 1:01:16.506
…are…

1:01:18.925 --> 1:01:19.801
one.

1:01:24.639 --> 1:01:25.640
Run!

1:01:26.224 --> 1:01:27.433
Run! Run! Run!

1:01:41.531 --> 1:01:42.782
Dustin!

1:01:47.537 --> 1:01:50.164
-Come on! Come on!
-Let's go!

1:01:52.625 --> 1:01:53.710
Come on!

1:01:55.336 --> 1:01:56.170
Shit!

1:02:08.975 --> 1:02:10.727
Come on, go! Go, go, go!

1:02:10.810 --> 1:02:12.228
Run! Run! Run!

1:03:12.747 --> 1:03:14.123
-She's hurting it.
-How?

1:03:14.207 --> 1:03:15.041
She's fighting Vecna.

1:03:15.124 --> 1:03:16.250
Hive mind.

1:03:26.427 --> 1:03:27.887
So…

1:03:28.638 --> 1:03:32.433
you truly do want to die.

1:03:39.857 --> 1:03:41.609
-We have to help her.
-How?

1:03:41.692 --> 1:03:45.154
The hive mind works in both ways.
If we hurt the Mind Flayer, we hurt Vecna.

1:03:45.238 --> 1:03:47.114
What, hurt Godzilla over there?

1:03:47.198 --> 1:03:50.243
The only way to damage anything
of that scale, we spread out.

1:03:50.326 --> 1:03:52.745
Flank it on all sides.
Just chip away at its hit points.

1:03:52.829 --> 1:03:54.664
"Hit points"? What are you talking about?

1:03:54.747 --> 1:03:55.790
There.

1:03:55.873 --> 1:03:59.836
One of us draws it to that canyon.
The rest take positions on those cliffs.

1:04:00.962 --> 1:04:02.129
Ambush it from above.

1:04:03.381 --> 1:04:05.091
There's just one question.

1:04:06.342 --> 1:04:07.760
Which one of us is bait?

1:04:10.346 --> 1:04:11.681
I am.

1:04:34.120 --> 1:04:35.246
Go!

1:04:35.329 --> 1:04:36.163
Go!

1:04:38.124 --> 1:04:39.125
Come on.

1:04:57.894 --> 1:04:58.895
No!

1:04:59.478 --> 1:05:00.396
No, no!

1:05:00.479 --> 1:05:02.857
There's nothing we can do!
Come on, please!

1:06:08.714 --> 1:06:11.258
Boom!

1:06:42.748 --> 1:06:44.333
Look out! Look out!

1:06:48.963 --> 1:06:51.674
-This is for Eddie, you son of a bitch!
-For Eddie!

1:07:32.757 --> 1:07:34.800
I'm not afraid anymore.

1:07:42.099 --> 1:07:43.059
We're not…

1:07:44.935 --> 1:07:45.978
afraid…

1:07:49.065 --> 1:07:50.149
of you.

1:08:05.081 --> 1:08:06.165
Yeah!

1:08:07.500 --> 1:08:08.626
We gotta go!

1:08:08.709 --> 1:08:10.086
Run! Shit, shit, shit!

1:08:48.874 --> 1:08:49.875
El!

1:08:53.546 --> 1:08:54.672
Is everyone okay?

1:08:56.590 --> 1:08:57.466
Holly.

1:09:21.490 --> 1:09:22.992
Holly? Can you hear me?

1:09:23.075 --> 1:09:24.326
Holly?

1:09:24.410 --> 1:09:27.037
Holly? Holly, come on. Come on.

1:09:40.801 --> 1:09:41.635
Nancy?

1:09:43.596 --> 1:09:46.473
Yeah. Yeah, it's me. I'm here.

1:09:46.557 --> 1:09:50.477
Yeah, it's me. I'm here. I'm here.

1:09:52.771 --> 1:09:54.148
Holly?

1:09:56.025 --> 1:09:56.901
Hey!

1:09:58.444 --> 1:09:59.445
Hey.

1:10:26.430 --> 1:10:29.767
Okay, get it all out.
You got this. You're gonna be okay.

1:10:30.392 --> 1:10:31.936
Where… Where am I?

1:10:32.019 --> 1:10:35.439
You're safe. You're safe, bud, okay?
We're here to get you home.

1:10:36.065 --> 1:10:37.358
Yeah. Whoa!

1:10:38.067 --> 1:10:41.237
I got you, bud. I got you.
I got you, bud. It's okay.

1:11:44.258 --> 1:11:46.677
Please, please. Come back to me!

1:11:46.760 --> 1:11:49.305
No!

1:11:59.273 --> 1:12:01.108
You fucked with the wrong family.

1:12:10.117 --> 1:12:11.994
Mom, you're killing him!

1:12:12.828 --> 1:12:14.246
Help!

1:12:16.999 --> 1:12:18.959
Why don't you go ahead and go home?

1:12:21.170 --> 1:12:23.130
I didn't run away this time.

1:12:23.213 --> 1:12:24.840
Eddie!

1:12:24.923 --> 1:12:25.966
I love you, man.

1:12:26.550 --> 1:12:27.885
Goodbye, Mike.

1:12:28.552 --> 1:12:30.929
El! El, where are you?

1:12:32.264 --> 1:12:34.850
He did not make me into this.

1:12:34.933 --> 1:12:36.101
You did.

1:12:38.937 --> 1:12:40.272
Will, wake up!

1:12:41.273 --> 1:12:42.524
Go away!

1:12:44.401 --> 1:12:46.236
I just want this to be over.

1:13:38.705 --> 1:13:41.458
-Chief, you copy? Chief?
-Yeah, yeah, I copy. What's going on?

1:13:41.542 --> 1:13:44.002
Well, the noseless bastard's toast.

1:13:44.086 --> 1:13:48.006
We're back in the Upside Down,
and we have the kids.

1:13:51.218 --> 1:13:53.429
How is everybody? Is everybody okay?

1:13:54.138 --> 1:13:56.723
Yeah, the party took a hell of a beating,
but we're okay.

1:13:58.225 --> 1:13:59.268
What about El?

1:14:00.936 --> 1:14:02.146
The whole party.

1:14:07.985 --> 1:14:10.154
So what do we say
you hit the music, old man?

1:14:10.237 --> 1:14:12.489
Destroy the Upside Down once and for all.

1:14:13.198 --> 1:14:14.950
Let's ditch this hellscape.

1:14:16.243 --> 1:14:17.369
Yeah, copy that.

1:14:34.761 --> 1:14:37.723
All right. The countdown begins.

1:14:51.195 --> 1:14:53.655
Hey, stop!
You're gonna get it all over me!

1:14:55.908 --> 1:14:58.035
Hey, hey, I'm nasty too.

1:14:58.619 --> 1:15:00.162
It does stink.

1:15:04.500 --> 1:15:08.170
How can you just leave me standing

1:15:08.253 --> 1:15:11.089
Alone in a world that's so cold?

1:15:11.173 --> 1:15:12.174
The world is so cold

1:15:12.257 --> 1:15:14.426
Maybe I'm just too demanding

1:15:16.011 --> 1:15:19.431
Maybe I'm just like my father
Too bold

1:15:19.515 --> 1:15:22.809
Maybe you're just like my mother

1:15:23.602 --> 1:15:26.271
She's never satisfied

1:15:26.897 --> 1:15:30.275
Why do we scream at each other?

1:15:31.485 --> 1:15:34.279
What are you doing? You're gonna let
more of that crap in here.

1:15:34.363 --> 1:15:37.115
It's either that or pass out.

1:15:37.199 --> 1:15:39.159
Because you smell like…

1:15:40.619 --> 1:15:43.705
I actually don't know what you smell like,
but it's bad.

1:15:55.342 --> 1:15:56.885
Assholes.

1:15:57.761 --> 1:15:59.096
Eh?

1:16:00.013 --> 1:16:01.306
That's good.

1:16:02.891 --> 1:16:04.851
There she is, home sweet home.

1:16:06.144 --> 1:16:09.106
So, Jimbo, I just gotta ask.
How does it feel?

1:16:09.648 --> 1:16:12.401
Feels like I need a nap and a smoke.

1:16:12.484 --> 1:16:14.069
-I thought you quit.
-Yeah.

1:16:14.152 --> 1:16:16.446
That's why it's gonna taste so good.

1:16:26.915 --> 1:16:28.000
Watch out!

1:16:33.964 --> 1:16:35.132
Everyone okay?

1:16:41.138 --> 1:16:43.348
Everyone put your hands up!

1:16:43.432 --> 1:16:44.766
I said, hands up!

1:16:44.850 --> 1:16:46.268
-Move!
-Hey! Get off me!

1:16:46.351 --> 1:16:48.562
Get down! Get down! Get your hands up!

1:16:49.563 --> 1:16:51.315
-I said hands up!
-Oh, wow!

1:16:51.398 --> 1:16:52.399
Okay, okay.

1:16:52.482 --> 1:16:53.775
Okay, okay.

1:16:55.068 --> 1:16:57.821
No! No! That's my sister! Let go of me!

1:16:57.904 --> 1:16:59.531
-Yeah, yeah!
-Okay, okay!

1:17:06.204 --> 1:17:07.539
Let's go! Move!

1:17:07.623 --> 1:17:09.666
-Dustin!
-Holly, what's happening?

1:17:10.250 --> 1:17:13.170
Everybody up! Everybody up!

1:17:14.171 --> 1:17:15.756
El? Do you see El?

1:17:16.465 --> 1:17:19.509
Sergeant! Where's the girl?

1:17:19.593 --> 1:17:21.928
She was right here one second ago.

1:17:25.766 --> 1:17:26.850
She must have escaped.

1:17:35.776 --> 1:17:36.610
Oh God.

1:17:40.614 --> 1:17:43.325
-Mike…
-Get off me! Get off me!

1:17:54.378 --> 1:17:55.295
You…

1:17:55.379 --> 1:17:57.964
You have to get out of there!
You have to get out!

1:17:58.048 --> 1:18:00.467
None of this will ever end,
not if I'm still here.

1:18:00.550 --> 1:18:04.054
No, no. We'll figure something out.
We'll fight back. We always do.

1:18:04.137 --> 1:18:06.056
I need you to talk to the others.

1:18:06.139 --> 1:18:09.476
-No. No.
-I need you to thank them for me.

1:18:09.559 --> 1:18:11.186
For being so kind to me.

1:18:12.020 --> 1:18:14.231
And teaching me what it means
to be a friend.

1:18:14.314 --> 1:18:16.108
No! Please don't do this.

1:18:16.191 --> 1:18:19.945
Mike, I need you
to help them understand my choice.

1:18:20.028 --> 1:18:21.613
But I don't. I don't understand.

1:18:21.697 --> 1:18:22.698
I know.

1:18:23.865 --> 1:18:24.991
But you will.

1:18:25.701 --> 1:18:26.868
One day, you will.

1:18:28.328 --> 1:18:29.830
You understand me.

1:18:32.457 --> 1:18:33.834
Better than anyone.

1:18:34.543 --> 1:18:36.169
You always have.

1:18:37.421 --> 1:18:38.922
From the day we met…

1:18:47.055 --> 1:18:48.390
…you've seen me.

1:18:48.974 --> 1:18:52.144
Well, my name's Mike. Short for Michael.

1:18:52.227 --> 1:18:54.980
Maybe we can call you El.
Short for Eleven.

1:18:59.359 --> 1:19:00.694
The real me.

1:19:00.777 --> 1:19:04.239
I never meant to cause you any sorrow

1:19:09.202 --> 1:19:11.997
I never meant to cause you any pain

1:19:17.377 --> 1:19:20.380
I only wanted one time
To see you laughing

1:19:21.423 --> 1:19:22.549
I love you.

1:19:23.884 --> 1:19:26.511
I love you for exactly who you are.

1:19:26.595 --> 1:19:30.474
I only wanted to see you laughing
In the purple rain

1:19:33.477 --> 1:19:35.479
Please don't leave me, El.

1:19:37.481 --> 1:19:39.399
Please don't do this.

1:19:41.026 --> 1:19:43.028
I will always be with you.

1:19:45.405 --> 1:19:46.698
I love you.

1:19:49.701 --> 1:19:53.747
Purple rain, purple rain

1:19:59.461 --> 1:20:00.420
Goodbye, Mike.

1:20:00.504 --> 1:20:02.672
Purple rain

1:20:02.756 --> 1:20:06.843
El! El! El! El! El!

1:20:06.927 --> 1:20:08.303
-El!
-Mike!

1:20:08.386 --> 1:20:09.763
-Hey, don't touch her!
-Mike!

1:20:13.475 --> 1:20:15.602
Get off me! Get off me!

1:20:15.685 --> 1:20:18.730
El! El! El!

1:20:20.065 --> 1:20:21.608
El!

1:20:27.697 --> 1:20:29.658
El, no!

1:20:29.741 --> 1:20:32.244
Eleven!

1:20:32.327 --> 1:20:34.788
El!

1:20:35.413 --> 1:20:39.501
El! El!

1:21:37.976 --> 1:21:41.479
No!

1:21:47.652 --> 1:21:50.155
El!

1:21:55.243 --> 1:21:58.580
El! El!

1:23:52.527 --> 1:23:54.320
-Check it out?
-Yeah.

1:24:03.079 --> 1:24:06.124
Hi there, strangers. It's been a while.

1:24:06.916 --> 1:24:08.668
I wonder… I mean…

1:24:09.169 --> 1:24:12.047
Do you guys… even remember me?

1:24:13.173 --> 1:24:15.675
Okay, maybe I'm being too modest.
I mean, let's be honest,

1:24:15.759 --> 1:24:19.637
who could forget this soothing voice
with a trace of a Debra Winger rasp?

1:24:20.263 --> 1:24:26.811
That's right. It's me,
Robin Buckley, aka Rockin' Robin.

1:24:26.895 --> 1:24:29.481
Jimmy "Fast Hands" was kind enough
to let me back into the booth

1:24:29.564 --> 1:24:31.066
for a guest stint,

1:24:31.149 --> 1:24:35.612
but you're gonna have to cut me some slack
because I am feeling rusty.

1:24:36.321 --> 1:24:38.573
I mean, what do I even talk about?
You know?

1:24:38.656 --> 1:24:43.745
My go-to subjects are as out of date
as, well, as my friend's bowl cut.

1:24:44.496 --> 1:24:47.082
I mean, there's no soldiers,

1:24:47.957 --> 1:24:49.250
no fences,

1:24:49.918 --> 1:24:52.003
no Big Brother cameras,

1:24:52.087 --> 1:24:55.465
and the only Big Mac I can find
is a Smush Double Patty at Mickey D's.

1:24:56.216 --> 1:25:01.054
People are happy and smiling
and going to the movies.

1:25:01.137 --> 1:25:04.182
But hey, who doesn't wanna see
Indy's new adventure?

1:25:04.265 --> 1:25:06.351
Shit. Uh…

1:25:07.727 --> 1:25:08.895
There we go.

1:25:10.355 --> 1:25:12.565
Sorry about that.
My partner in crime ditched me.

1:25:12.649 --> 1:25:15.735
But, well, as far as excuses go,

1:25:16.694 --> 1:25:18.071
he had a pretty good one.

1:25:18.154 --> 1:25:20.782
Let's go, boys!
Baseball ready! Baseball ready!

1:25:20.865 --> 1:25:23.118
-Now…
-No mental mistakes!

1:25:23.201 --> 1:25:26.162
…I am almost
too superstitious to say this,

1:25:26.246 --> 1:25:27.956
and I'm knocking on some wood here,

1:25:28.039 --> 1:25:33.044
but I think the Hawkins curse
has finally lifted.

1:25:33.128 --> 1:25:35.255
All right, Thomas.
Let's go. Here we go, man!

1:25:35.338 --> 1:25:37.048
-But at the same time…
-Let's go.

1:25:37.632 --> 1:25:40.343
…this isn't even the Hawkins
that I remember.

1:25:41.553 --> 1:25:43.263
It feels so different.

1:25:44.973 --> 1:25:46.641
But maybe it's not the town.

1:25:47.350 --> 1:25:49.769
Maybe it's me that's changed.

1:25:51.187 --> 1:25:52.689
We probably all have.

1:25:54.482 --> 1:25:57.986
At least, that's certainly true
of my friends.

1:25:58.528 --> 1:26:02.782
Who, by the way, are graduating today.

1:26:06.786 --> 1:26:10.957
That's right, Hawkins High class of '89
is walking the podium today.

1:26:11.040 --> 1:26:13.543
I hope you all come out and support them.
I know I will.

1:26:13.626 --> 1:26:16.379
Because if anyone deserves a standing O,
they do.

1:26:16.462 --> 1:26:20.675
So to get their party started,
a new favorite.

1:26:33.062 --> 1:26:35.982
You break any more bones,
you're on your own.

1:26:36.566 --> 1:26:39.110
Because I am done with hospitals.

1:26:39.194 --> 1:26:40.904
Maybe I should be on my own.

1:26:40.987 --> 1:26:41.988
I mean…

1:26:42.572 --> 1:26:43.990
what is going on here?

1:26:44.073 --> 1:26:46.201
What? We're graduating today.

1:26:46.284 --> 1:26:49.537
In two hours.
I think you're getting ahead of yourself.

1:26:50.622 --> 1:26:51.664
Hmm.

1:26:53.124 --> 1:26:55.919
Okay, now you're definitely
getting ahead of yourself.

1:26:56.502 --> 1:26:59.797
I'm sorry. You're just looking,
uh, super sexy right now.

1:27:00.465 --> 1:27:02.383
And you're looking super dorky.

1:27:05.220 --> 1:27:07.222
Here comes your man

1:27:08.932 --> 1:27:10.934
Here comes your man

1:27:11.017 --> 1:27:14.604
Ugh, gag me with a spoon.

1:27:16.731 --> 1:27:18.816
Here comes your man

1:27:18.900 --> 1:27:20.443
You gonna take the picture?

1:27:20.526 --> 1:27:22.695
Already? Please?

1:27:23.279 --> 1:27:26.032
Ma, it's okay.

1:27:26.115 --> 1:27:28.493
-I'm only a day's drive away.
-I know.

1:27:28.576 --> 1:27:30.203
I'm gonna come home
every chance that I get.

1:27:30.286 --> 1:27:31.120
Okay.

1:27:31.204 --> 1:27:33.706
I'm gonna call you so much
that you're gonna wanna change numbers.

1:27:33.790 --> 1:27:34.999
-Okay.
-Okay?

1:27:35.083 --> 1:27:36.584
Okay.

1:27:36.668 --> 1:27:38.002
-I love you.
-I love you.

1:27:38.086 --> 1:27:39.629
Do you wanna take more pictures?

1:27:39.712 --> 1:27:40.672
-Yeah.
-Okay.

1:27:40.755 --> 1:27:44.676
Ooh, so handsome. My valedictorian.

1:27:46.177 --> 1:27:47.512
Superman!

1:27:47.595 --> 1:27:49.430
-All right, rolling.
-Happy graduation.

1:27:49.514 --> 1:27:51.140
Happy graduation.

1:27:51.224 --> 1:27:52.517
-That's nice.
-Class of '89.

1:27:52.600 --> 1:27:53.601
Yeah.

1:27:53.685 --> 1:27:55.520
Shit. Hold on. No, no.

1:27:55.603 --> 1:27:57.355
-Oh God. No.
-Let him hang it back up.

1:27:57.438 --> 1:27:59.482
-Leave the bedsheet.
-No, no, no.

1:27:59.565 --> 1:28:01.067
There's too much light.
It needs diffusion.

1:28:01.150 --> 1:28:03.278
-It's not The Godfather.
-I know it's not.

1:28:03.361 --> 1:28:05.822
-Let him hang it up.
-You get one more take.

1:28:08.533 --> 1:28:10.576
It's been all day 'cause of the artist…

1:28:10.660 --> 1:28:13.246
-Hello?
-Joyce. This is Karen. Have you seen Mike?

1:28:13.329 --> 1:28:15.081
No, I haven't seen him.

1:28:15.164 --> 1:28:17.208
We haven't seen him since last night.

1:28:17.292 --> 1:28:20.253
It's Karen. She can't find Mike.

1:28:22.755 --> 1:28:25.466
Here comes your man

1:28:46.362 --> 1:28:49.699
El! El!

1:28:51.034 --> 1:28:52.702
El!

1:28:53.870 --> 1:28:54.829
Hey, kid.

1:28:58.666 --> 1:29:00.251
Thought I might find you here.

1:29:04.172 --> 1:29:05.465
Your mom's freaking out.

1:29:06.674 --> 1:29:08.509
Can't say I blame her. I mean…

1:29:09.385 --> 1:29:11.888
I don't know if you remember,
but we do have a history

1:29:11.971 --> 1:29:14.057
of kids going missing in this town.

1:29:16.851 --> 1:29:18.603
She won't understand.

1:29:19.187 --> 1:29:24.192
She'll never understand why I can't do it,
why I can't walk the stage.

1:29:25.777 --> 1:29:27.070
It'd be like a lie.

1:29:29.155 --> 1:29:31.949
Like I'm okay with moving on.

1:29:32.033 --> 1:29:33.451
And I'm not.

1:29:35.995 --> 1:29:37.288
I'm not okay with it.

1:29:41.209 --> 1:29:42.502
I had this plan.

1:29:43.461 --> 1:29:48.257
That me and El, we were gonna go
someplace far away,

1:29:48.341 --> 1:29:49.926
and… and no one would find us.

1:29:51.219 --> 1:29:54.931
And I said this thing about going
somewhere with three waterfalls.

1:29:55.014 --> 1:29:57.475
I mean, I… I don't even know
if she believed me.

1:29:58.393 --> 1:30:03.773
Who would? Three waterfalls?
I mean, that's so stupid, childish.

1:30:04.524 --> 1:30:07.735
It was a fantasy plan.
I should've had a real one.

1:30:09.821 --> 1:30:10.863
I just didn't…

1:30:12.615 --> 1:30:15.243
I didn't think that she would just…

1:30:15.326 --> 1:30:16.869
Hey, hey. This…

1:30:21.207 --> 1:30:23.000
It's not your… It's not your fault.

1:30:25.336 --> 1:30:27.171
What happened is not your fault.

1:30:29.173 --> 1:30:30.925
El made her choice.

1:30:32.385 --> 1:30:34.470
Now it's time for you to make yours.

1:30:35.513 --> 1:30:38.349
And the way I see it,
you got two roads ahead of you.

1:30:39.183 --> 1:30:40.685
You got one road

1:30:41.644 --> 1:30:43.896
where you keep blaming yourself
for what happened.

1:30:43.980 --> 1:30:47.233
You keep going over it in your head,
what you could've done differently.

1:30:48.025 --> 1:30:53.156
You push people away, and you suffer,
because that's what you think you deserve.

1:30:55.533 --> 1:30:57.410
And then there's another road…

1:31:00.913 --> 1:31:05.710
where you find a way
to accept what happened.

1:31:06.794 --> 1:31:08.921
Find a way to accept her choice.

1:31:10.214 --> 1:31:13.301
Doesn't mean you gotta like it.
Doesn't mean you gotta understand it.

1:31:14.093 --> 1:31:15.678
And never think about it.

1:31:17.930 --> 1:31:19.223
You just accept it.

1:31:20.808 --> 1:31:23.436
And you live the best goddamn life
you can.

1:31:29.484 --> 1:31:31.777
I've been down that first road before.

1:31:34.322 --> 1:31:35.781
And I don't recommend it.

1:31:38.075 --> 1:31:39.494
And as for El…

1:31:40.745 --> 1:31:43.748
I think you know
what she would have wanted for you.

1:32:05.770 --> 1:32:08.064
-I don't know. Me?
-Yeah.

1:32:08.147 --> 1:32:11.567
-Never been.
-Me neither. But I think she'd like it.

1:32:29.794 --> 1:32:31.045
Good afternoon, everyone,

1:32:31.128 --> 1:32:35.132
and welcome to the graduation ceremony
for the class of '89.

1:32:39.804 --> 1:32:41.806
Mom! Mom!

1:32:49.480 --> 1:32:51.023
Mike.

1:32:51.732 --> 1:32:53.776
I'm sorry, Mom. I panicked.

1:32:54.819 --> 1:32:56.362
You don't have to explain.

1:32:57.697 --> 1:32:58.906
God, look at you.

1:33:01.909 --> 1:33:03.286
You're all grown up.

1:33:04.579 --> 1:33:05.997
I'm so proud of you.

1:33:08.040 --> 1:33:10.501
I'm so, so proud.

1:33:17.466 --> 1:33:18.467
I love you, Mom.

1:33:20.803 --> 1:33:22.221
I love you, baby.

1:33:24.807 --> 1:33:27.768
And now it's my great pleasure
to introduce someone

1:33:27.852 --> 1:33:31.272
who has truly excelled
during their time here.

1:33:31.355 --> 1:33:37.320
Ladies and gentlemen, give a warm welcome
for your valedictorian, Dustin Henderson.

1:33:39.363 --> 1:33:40.406
Yeah, buddy!

1:33:41.866 --> 1:33:43.117
Dustin!

1:33:43.200 --> 1:33:44.118
That's my friend!

1:33:44.201 --> 1:33:45.244
Whoo!

1:33:51.584 --> 1:33:54.420
I just wanted a normal childhood.

1:33:55.254 --> 1:33:57.214
But that childhood was stolen from me.

1:33:58.549 --> 1:34:00.426
It was stolen from us.

1:34:01.302 --> 1:34:03.929
And this past year,
if you wanna know the truth,

1:34:04.013 --> 1:34:06.349
I've been pretty pissed off about it.

1:34:06.432 --> 1:34:07.308
Language.

1:34:07.391 --> 1:34:09.352
But then I thought back
to the past six years,

1:34:09.435 --> 1:34:13.856
and I realized that,
even though there was a lot of bad,

1:34:15.024 --> 1:34:16.901
there was so much good too.

1:34:18.778 --> 1:34:21.030
There's this game I like to play.

1:34:21.113 --> 1:34:23.199
It's called Dungeons & Dragons.

1:34:23.282 --> 1:34:24.784
-Yup!
-Jesus Christ.

1:34:24.867 --> 1:34:28.329
And in this game,
there are two types of chaos classes,

1:34:28.412 --> 1:34:30.623
chaotic good and chaotic bad.

1:34:31.582 --> 1:34:36.295
Now, bad chaos brings
anarchy, destruction, war.

1:34:36.379 --> 1:34:40.257
But good chaos can bring innovation,

1:34:41.425 --> 1:34:42.426
change.

1:34:43.010 --> 1:34:44.303
And this school,

1:34:45.513 --> 1:34:47.473
frankly, it needed to change.

1:34:47.556 --> 1:34:53.229
Because we were so divided
into the jocks, the nerds, freaks.

1:34:53.312 --> 1:34:54.772
And in the chaos,

1:34:55.398 --> 1:34:58.359
all those walls broke down,

1:34:58.984 --> 1:35:00.444
and I made new friends.

1:35:01.195 --> 1:35:04.407
I made friends who were never even
supposed to be my friends.

1:35:04.990 --> 1:35:07.201
This wasn't just me.
I saw this happen with so many others.

1:35:08.035 --> 1:35:10.538
When you get to know people
who are different from you,

1:35:10.621 --> 1:35:13.582
you begin to learn more about yourself.

1:35:14.458 --> 1:35:15.292
You change.

1:35:16.877 --> 1:35:18.087
You grow.

1:35:18.587 --> 1:35:21.132
I'm a better person now.

1:35:21.215 --> 1:35:23.634
I'm a better person because of them,

1:35:24.218 --> 1:35:26.053
because of my friends.

1:35:27.012 --> 1:35:30.099
So, I'm not pissed off anymore.

1:35:31.225 --> 1:35:32.643
But I am worried.

1:35:33.394 --> 1:35:34.228
Worried,

1:35:35.271 --> 1:35:37.440
because now that the chaos is over,

1:35:37.982 --> 1:35:40.776
Principal Higgins
and every square like him

1:35:40.860 --> 1:35:43.863
is gonna do their damnedest
to put everything back in order.

1:35:43.946 --> 1:35:45.823
And I don't want order,

1:35:45.906 --> 1:35:48.367
which is why it's hypocritical
that I'm wearing this thing.

1:35:48.451 --> 1:35:52.037
I mean, we look ridiculous.
What is this? We look like Roman senators.

1:35:52.121 --> 1:35:55.750
I mean, it's not who I am.
I don't think it's who any of us are.

1:35:55.833 --> 1:35:58.919
So, honestly, just screw it.

1:35:59.003 --> 1:36:00.880
-Henderson.
-Yes!

1:36:00.963 --> 1:36:03.174
-Screw the school.
-Henderson! Henderson!

1:36:03.257 --> 1:36:04.633
-Screw the system.
-That's enough!

1:36:04.717 --> 1:36:05.801
Screw conformity.

1:36:05.885 --> 1:36:07.303
-Screw everyone and everything…
-Yes!

1:36:07.386 --> 1:36:09.388
…trying to hold you back
and tear us apart,

1:36:09.472 --> 1:36:12.308
because this, this is our year!

1:36:12.391 --> 1:36:13.809
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

1:36:13.893 --> 1:36:15.019
Yeah!

1:36:16.061 --> 1:36:16.896
Whoo!

1:36:16.979 --> 1:36:18.397
Whoo-hoo!

1:36:25.821 --> 1:36:28.532
The bugle sounds, the charge begins

1:36:29.033 --> 1:36:32.036
But on this battlefield, no one wins

1:36:32.119 --> 1:36:34.914
The smell of acrid smoke
And horses' breath

1:36:35.414 --> 1:36:37.708
As I plunge on into certain death

1:36:40.002 --> 1:36:41.462
Whoo-hoo!

1:36:43.255 --> 1:36:44.465
Settle down!

1:36:45.466 --> 1:36:47.259
Back in your seats now!

1:36:48.302 --> 1:36:51.138
Summer school for all of you!

1:36:51.222 --> 1:36:52.765
And detention!

1:37:09.615 --> 1:37:10.699
-Dustin!
-Dustin!

1:37:10.783 --> 1:37:11.826
Dustin!

1:37:13.911 --> 1:37:16.205
You're a madman.
You're an absolute madman.

1:37:16.288 --> 1:37:19.250
-Higgins totally shit his pants.
-What's he gonna do, expel me?

1:37:19.333 --> 1:37:20.876
-You're crazy.
-Hey.

1:37:21.794 --> 1:37:23.462
Hey, Stacey.

1:37:23.546 --> 1:37:26.298
I just wanted to say what you did up there
was pretty badass.

1:37:26.382 --> 1:37:29.885
Oh. Thanks. I was kind of just going
for a bit of a Belushi thing.

1:37:30.845 --> 1:37:32.680
But if he was in like a Hughes film.

1:37:32.763 --> 1:37:34.723
But I don't know. Does that make sense?

1:37:34.807 --> 1:37:35.683
Yeah.

1:37:35.766 --> 1:37:37.268
-That's okay if you…
-No, totally.

1:37:37.351 --> 1:37:39.103
-Yeah?
-Mm-hmm.

1:37:41.063 --> 1:37:42.189
Okay. Cool.

1:37:43.232 --> 1:37:44.942
-Why'd I say that?
-Dude…

1:37:45.025 --> 1:37:48.821
Hey, so I'm having a party later tonight.

1:37:49.363 --> 1:37:50.865
You guys should come.

1:37:51.991 --> 1:37:53.909
-Wait.
-Did that just happen?

1:37:53.993 --> 1:37:55.619
Should we go?

1:37:55.703 --> 1:37:57.705
Is that rhetorical?

1:37:58.205 --> 1:38:00.124
No. Screw that.

1:38:00.207 --> 1:38:01.458
I got a better idea.

1:38:02.001 --> 1:38:03.002
Way better.

1:38:05.963 --> 1:38:08.966
I'm just saying, I think
you guys would really dig New York.

1:38:09.049 --> 1:38:10.593
-Yeah.
-How much is rent?

1:38:10.676 --> 1:38:13.387
-Thinking about moving?
-You wanna come live with me?

1:38:13.470 --> 1:38:15.055
You're serious? Come on.

1:38:15.139 --> 1:38:18.976
I mean, look at this place.
The sunset, the view.

1:38:20.144 --> 1:38:21.353
Whoo!

1:38:21.854 --> 1:38:24.523
You guys are seriously telling me
you don't miss any of this?

1:38:24.607 --> 1:38:25.482
Mm.

1:38:25.566 --> 1:38:26.692
No.

1:38:26.775 --> 1:38:30.821
The forest, the quarry,
Family Video, the Hawk?

1:38:30.905 --> 1:38:32.448
No.

1:38:32.531 --> 1:38:35.367
No, I couldn't come back here
if you paid me a million bucks.

1:38:35.451 --> 1:38:38.537
Mm. You'd need a lot less than a million,
I'll tell you that.

1:38:38.621 --> 1:38:40.623
Prices are still way down.

1:38:42.124 --> 1:38:44.418
There's actually this rad place
over in Forest Hills.

1:38:44.501 --> 1:38:47.630
I can't quite afford it yet,
but I'm close.

1:38:47.713 --> 1:38:49.798
And that is on a coach's salary.

1:38:49.882 --> 1:38:51.884
-Don't forget sex ed teacher.
-That's true.

1:38:51.967 --> 1:38:53.469
They have you teaching sex ed?

1:38:54.053 --> 1:38:56.096
It's part of the gig.

1:38:56.180 --> 1:38:59.308
If I had a question about an STD,
you'd be the first person I'd come to.

1:38:59.391 --> 1:39:00.643
Thank you?

1:39:02.061 --> 1:39:03.103
No, I love it.

1:39:03.187 --> 1:39:05.022
I love teaching these kids, you know?

1:39:05.105 --> 1:39:07.316
I get to teach them
about the miracle of life,

1:39:07.399 --> 1:39:11.946
and how to not start it accidentally.

1:39:12.029 --> 1:39:14.657
And this time,
I'm in control of the grades.

1:39:14.740 --> 1:39:17.409
And why do I feel
like you go pretty easy there?

1:39:17.493 --> 1:39:18.869
I have a strict A policy.

1:39:18.953 --> 1:39:21.580
-Uh-huh.
-B, if you're a real knucklehead.

1:39:21.664 --> 1:39:22.873
That's about as low as I go.

1:39:22.957 --> 1:39:24.750
Hell, can you come and teach at NYU?

1:39:25.876 --> 1:39:28.504
I mean, what, I'm gonna grade your movie

1:39:28.587 --> 1:39:31.548
about capitalism,
cannibalism, or whatever?

1:39:31.632 --> 1:39:33.801
No, it's anti-capitalist. The Consumer.

1:39:33.884 --> 1:39:37.972
It's a metaphor. The more she eats,
the hungrier she gets.

1:39:38.055 --> 1:39:39.348
-Right.
-Okay.

1:39:39.431 --> 1:39:41.350
-Well, I mean, it's a working…
-Obviously.

1:39:41.433 --> 1:39:43.852
-That's the working title.
-It's good.

1:39:43.936 --> 1:39:45.270
Mm-hmm.

1:39:46.397 --> 1:39:49.650
Now, Smith. Smith, I… I would consider.

1:39:49.733 --> 1:39:50.693
Oh, really?

1:39:50.776 --> 1:39:53.195
Is it the lectures on Steinem
that draw you

1:39:53.278 --> 1:39:55.114
or the high concentration of women?

1:39:55.906 --> 1:39:58.033
Can't it be both?

1:39:59.368 --> 1:40:00.869
What about you, Nance?

1:40:00.953 --> 1:40:02.371
How are the babes at Emerson?

1:40:02.955 --> 1:40:03.789
Oh, um…

1:40:04.957 --> 1:40:06.041
I wouldn't know.

1:40:07.960 --> 1:40:09.086
I dropped out.

1:40:09.670 --> 1:40:10.838
No way. What?

1:40:10.921 --> 1:40:14.049
Ho, ho, ho! I knew it.
You became a Navy SEAL.

1:40:14.133 --> 1:40:16.135
Oh no, not quite. I…

1:40:16.218 --> 1:40:18.387
I took a job at the Herald.

1:40:18.470 --> 1:40:22.057
Which… It sounds fancier like that.
It's a trainee position.

1:40:22.141 --> 1:40:24.893
But I don't know.
I was just sick of school

1:40:24.977 --> 1:40:30.858
and thought I'd maybe get out there
and… try the real world.

1:40:32.776 --> 1:40:34.111
Nancy Wheeler.

1:40:35.112 --> 1:40:36.405
Still full of surprises.

1:40:42.161 --> 1:40:43.203
You know,

1:40:44.621 --> 1:40:47.875
there actually is something
that I miss about this place.

1:40:48.876 --> 1:40:50.002
I miss this.

1:40:51.003 --> 1:40:51.920
Just…

1:40:52.504 --> 1:40:53.672
us.

1:40:54.298 --> 1:40:55.215
Hanging out.

1:40:57.801 --> 1:40:58.969
I miss you guys.

1:41:01.638 --> 1:41:03.140
I really like my new friends.

1:41:04.933 --> 1:41:05.934
But it's…

1:41:06.643 --> 1:41:08.103
It's not the same.

1:41:11.398 --> 1:41:13.025
I don't think it ever will be.

1:41:23.702 --> 1:41:25.037
Okay, Jesus.

1:41:26.538 --> 1:41:27.915
You're killing me, man.

1:41:27.998 --> 1:41:29.625
Let's do something about it.

1:41:31.794 --> 1:41:33.212
I don't know. We could…

1:41:34.463 --> 1:41:35.464
meet up.

1:41:36.799 --> 1:41:38.050
Once a month, here.

1:41:38.634 --> 1:41:43.055
Yeah, or… or maybe somewhere
just more neutral.

1:41:43.138 --> 1:41:44.389
-Like…
-Okay.

1:41:44.473 --> 1:41:48.310
What's a city between Hawkins,
and Massachusetts, New York?

1:41:48.393 --> 1:41:49.394
Louisville.

1:41:50.062 --> 1:41:51.313
-Uh, Philly.
-Philly.

1:41:51.396 --> 1:41:54.441
I have an uncle who lives in Philly.
He's weird, but he's got a big house.

1:41:54.525 --> 1:41:56.944
-Does it have a basement?
-Yeah.

1:41:57.027 --> 1:41:58.821
-And a boiler room?
-A boiler room?

1:41:58.904 --> 1:41:59.905
Yeah.

1:42:00.030 --> 1:42:02.825
Oh my God, it's perfect.
You know, for the hideout.

1:42:02.908 --> 1:42:05.953
You know, where she traps all the men
and then burns their bodies.

1:42:06.912 --> 1:42:07.955
-The Consumer.
-The Consumer.

1:42:08.038 --> 1:42:10.874
-What do you think I'm talking about?
-I thought you were trying to kill us.

1:42:10.958 --> 1:42:11.959
Oh no.

1:42:12.042 --> 1:42:17.297
Okay, okay. Yeah, so we'll meet
at Robin's weird uncle's house,

1:42:17.381 --> 1:42:18.966
and we'll drink and reminisce

1:42:19.049 --> 1:42:23.679
and make Jonathan's
anti-capitalist cannibal movie.

1:42:25.139 --> 1:42:27.099
Starting next month.

1:42:29.226 --> 1:42:30.144
Yeah, I'm in.

1:42:32.020 --> 1:42:33.021
I'm in.

1:42:37.484 --> 1:42:39.570
To nothing ever keeping us apart.

1:42:41.113 --> 1:42:43.949
Including overbearing significant others.

1:42:44.950 --> 1:42:46.076
School.

1:42:46.910 --> 1:42:47.828
Mortgages.

1:42:48.704 --> 1:42:49.538
And kids.

1:42:50.706 --> 1:42:52.332
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

1:42:58.422 --> 1:43:00.674
Yeah, Steve. Kids?

1:43:00.757 --> 1:43:03.969
I don't know, guys.
I think Kristen might be the one.

1:43:06.555 --> 1:43:09.558
So, didn't you say the same thing
about Dawn?

1:43:09.641 --> 1:43:10.976
-No.
-And Margaret.

1:43:11.059 --> 1:43:11.935
And Julie.

1:43:12.019 --> 1:43:15.105
I did not say that about Julie.
She was drama from the start.

1:43:15.189 --> 1:43:16.023
Drama?

1:43:16.523 --> 1:43:18.734
Like, is she a good actor?

1:43:18.817 --> 1:43:20.068
Yeah, you do not wanna…

1:43:20.152 --> 1:43:21.236
I mean, I'm looking.

1:43:21.320 --> 1:43:23.906
-No, no, no. Not there.
-Yeah, have her come along.

1:43:47.179 --> 1:43:51.475
Chief. Mrs. Byers. Always a pleasure.

1:43:51.558 --> 1:43:53.060
Are we ready to order?

1:43:53.143 --> 1:43:54.561
Uh, yeah.

1:43:54.645 --> 1:44:00.150
Yeah. We're gonna have a bottle
of the Cabernet Sauv…

1:44:00.943 --> 1:44:03.737
-Sauvignon.
-Yeah. Cabernet Sauvignon.

1:44:03.820 --> 1:44:07.366
And we'll have some caviar to start.

1:44:07.449 --> 1:44:10.744
And we will have
two of the filet specials,

1:44:10.827 --> 1:44:13.038
however the chef would like
to prepare them.

1:44:13.538 --> 1:44:14.998
-Very good, sir.
-Okay.

1:44:15.082 --> 1:44:16.333
-Hop!
-What?

1:44:16.416 --> 1:44:19.628
It's a big day.
It's a once-in-a-lifetime day.

1:44:20.379 --> 1:44:23.632
You raised two beautiful boys
into incredible men.

1:44:23.715 --> 1:44:26.593
They had a lot more to overcome
than just puberty.

1:44:27.386 --> 1:44:28.637
You should be happy.

1:44:30.555 --> 1:44:32.057
You should be proud.

1:44:32.683 --> 1:44:33.976
I am, but…

1:44:34.643 --> 1:44:35.727
It's just…

1:44:36.353 --> 1:44:37.896
It's gonna be quiet in that cabin.

1:44:37.980 --> 1:44:40.023
It's just us and the crickets.

1:44:40.107 --> 1:44:44.528
Ugh, the crickets. Yeah. I don't like
the sound of those crickets anymore.

1:44:44.611 --> 1:44:45.529
Thank you.

1:44:46.280 --> 1:44:47.531
I wish, uh…

1:44:47.614 --> 1:44:49.741
I wish it was the sound
of something different.

1:44:49.825 --> 1:44:52.869
Maybe, um, squawk of seagulls

1:44:52.953 --> 1:44:57.249
or, uh, waves gently lapping on the beach.

1:44:57.332 --> 1:45:00.294
Well, that sounds nice.

1:45:01.295 --> 1:45:02.296
Could be real.

1:45:05.173 --> 1:45:08.051
I'm just saying there's nothing
tying us down here anymore.

1:45:08.135 --> 1:45:12.431
But you seem to think
our bank account is bigger than it is.

1:45:12.514 --> 1:45:13.348
Could be.

1:45:13.432 --> 1:45:15.726
I got a call from my buddy
in the New York days.

1:45:15.809 --> 1:45:17.811
Montauk's looking
for a new chief of police.

1:45:18.603 --> 1:45:21.815
Town's up and coming. It'd be 20% more.

1:45:21.898 --> 1:45:24.067
I know that's not big enough
for a mansion or anything,

1:45:24.151 --> 1:45:26.361
but it's… significant.

1:45:26.445 --> 1:45:29.948
Kids would be closer.
Just a little quick trip into the city.

1:45:30.449 --> 1:45:31.450
You and me?

1:45:32.659 --> 1:45:33.910
We could start again.

1:45:34.453 --> 1:45:35.454
Fresh.

1:45:36.705 --> 1:45:37.622
Together.

1:45:37.706 --> 1:45:39.124
Are you kidding?

1:45:39.207 --> 1:45:40.917
We don't have to figure out
anything tonight.

1:45:41.001 --> 1:45:42.961
We don't have to decide anything, but, um…

1:45:45.505 --> 1:45:46.965
That's not true.

1:45:47.049 --> 1:45:47.924
What…?

1:45:49.760 --> 1:45:52.596
There's one thing
I would like to decide tonight.

1:46:04.983 --> 1:46:05.942
Who's…?

1:46:13.450 --> 1:46:16.953
At last

1:46:17.037 --> 1:46:18.121
Joyce Byers.

1:46:19.331 --> 1:46:22.584
My love has come along

1:46:22.667 --> 1:46:24.753
Will you spend the rest of your life

1:46:25.337 --> 1:46:30.842
with a tired, grumpy, stubborn old man
who loves you very much?

1:46:33.845 --> 1:46:36.640
Yes. I will.

1:46:42.813 --> 1:46:47.484
Oh, well, at last

1:46:50.612 --> 1:46:54.408
The skies above are blue

1:46:57.911 --> 1:47:02.916
My heart was wrapped up in clover

1:47:05.836 --> 1:47:10.632
The night that I looked at you

1:47:11.174 --> 1:47:16.888
At last

1:47:22.978 --> 1:47:26.648
Ooh

1:47:33.697 --> 1:47:36.032
A hushed quiet falls over the town.

1:47:36.992 --> 1:47:40.454
Frightened villagers watch
from rooftops and alleyways, wondering,

1:47:40.537 --> 1:47:42.038
how will this all end?

1:47:43.165 --> 1:47:46.418
The sound of boots echo across the square

1:47:46.501 --> 1:47:49.421
as Strahd von Zarovich strides up
to Dustin the Bard.

1:47:49.504 --> 1:47:51.089
-Don't do this.
-The vampire lord lunges.

1:47:51.173 --> 1:47:52.924
-No!
-Plunging its fangs into his throat.

1:47:53.008 --> 1:47:55.177
Onlookers gasp as his body collapses.

1:47:55.260 --> 1:47:59.347
His lute clatters across the cobblestone,
letting out a final mournful note.

1:47:59.431 --> 1:48:00.390
Son of a bitch!

1:48:00.474 --> 1:48:04.769
A lone hero remains, Will the Wise,
Barovia's last and only hope.

1:48:04.853 --> 1:48:07.439
Cast Meteor Swarm. Take out the bastard.

1:48:07.522 --> 1:48:08.815
-I can't.
-Why not?

1:48:08.899 --> 1:48:11.026
He's in the range
of the suppression stone. No magic.

1:48:11.109 --> 1:48:12.861
Then just whack him with your staff.

1:48:12.944 --> 1:48:15.864
And inflict six points of damage.
He has 30 HP left.

1:48:17.782 --> 1:48:18.950
Okay, so now what?

1:48:19.034 --> 1:48:21.786
-That's it.
-Nothing.

1:48:22.370 --> 1:48:23.622
What do you mean, nothing?

1:48:25.081 --> 1:48:26.625
-Checkmate.
-We lost.

1:48:26.708 --> 1:48:30.962
So after all of that,
Strahd von Douchebag just wins?

1:48:31.963 --> 1:48:34.841
-This game is bullshit!
-I agree.

1:48:34.925 --> 1:48:37.761
Stupid, goddamn waste of time!

1:48:37.844 --> 1:48:40.764
Strahd takes great pleasure in your anger.

1:48:44.643 --> 1:48:47.187
Time to join your friends, sorcerer.

1:48:47.270 --> 1:48:50.398
Just get it over with and roll.
I don't wanna hear his shit anymore.

1:48:50.482 --> 1:48:51.483
All right.

1:48:56.196 --> 1:49:00.450
The mage. From the Abbey of St. Markovia.
She said we can summon her.

1:49:01.493 --> 1:49:02.702
When at our lowest depth.

1:49:03.286 --> 1:49:05.622
The incantation to summon her.
What's the incantation?

1:49:05.705 --> 1:49:08.291
-What is the incantation?
-Will! Will!

1:49:08.375 --> 1:49:12.796
"Oh, mage! Arise and end our fall
from darkened paths and secrets deep."

1:49:12.879 --> 1:49:15.382
"Come forth and help your promise keep."

1:49:17.259 --> 1:49:18.260
Nothing happens.

1:49:18.343 --> 1:49:20.095
-Come on, man.
-Why?

1:49:20.178 --> 1:49:21.972
Then why do we even have the incantation?

1:49:22.055 --> 1:49:23.390
-What?
-Wait.

1:49:23.473 --> 1:49:24.516
Wait, wait.

1:49:25.141 --> 1:49:27.686
A purple light begins to shine
through the mist.

1:49:27.769 --> 1:49:29.854
Growing brighter and brighter.

1:49:31.064 --> 1:49:31.982
It's a portal.

1:49:33.233 --> 1:49:35.151
And out of this portal steps…

1:49:35.777 --> 1:49:37.821
the Mage of St. Markovia!

1:49:42.659 --> 1:49:46.871
The mage holds out her hands, and shoom,
a beam of powerful light shoots forward.

1:49:46.955 --> 1:49:48.915
Strahd lets out a piercing…

1:49:48.999 --> 1:49:52.669
…as his body shrivels, burns,
and turns to ash.

1:49:54.045 --> 1:49:55.922
Bada-boom!

1:49:56.506 --> 1:49:58.883
How do you like that?

1:49:59.801 --> 1:50:01.469
Whoo!

1:50:02.178 --> 1:50:05.140
The misty gloom that shrouds the village
of Barovia evaporates,

1:50:05.223 --> 1:50:07.434
and you are met
with cheers from the townsfolk.

1:50:07.517 --> 1:50:10.270
In honor of your courage and bravery,
they give you medals,

1:50:10.353 --> 1:50:13.315
and you are all awarded
1,000 pieces of gold each.

1:50:15.317 --> 1:50:16.526
Flush with wealth and honor,

1:50:16.610 --> 1:50:19.696
you live out the rest of your lives
in comfort and in happiness.

1:50:19.779 --> 1:50:21.781
Aaaaah!

1:50:21.865 --> 1:50:23.325
The end.

1:50:23.408 --> 1:50:25.619
-Great campaign.
-Good campaign, buddy.

1:50:25.702 --> 1:50:26.661
Great campaign.

1:50:27.829 --> 1:50:30.123
Wait, wait, wait. Hold on. That's it?

1:50:30.206 --> 1:50:34.044
Comfort and happiness?
Could you be more trite?

1:50:34.127 --> 1:50:36.504
I thought you were some kind
of master storyteller or something.

1:50:37.297 --> 1:50:39.090
Oh.

1:50:44.721 --> 1:50:47.849
Well, it is true,
the comfort and happiness part.

1:50:48.850 --> 1:50:51.353
But happiness can be found in many places.

1:50:52.562 --> 1:50:55.148
The knight and the zoomer,

1:50:55.982 --> 1:50:59.152
they retire from battle,
and they settle down in a small village.

1:51:01.029 --> 1:51:02.656
With each passing day,

1:51:03.531 --> 1:51:05.200
their love grows stronger.

1:51:17.879 --> 1:51:18.880
The bard,

1:51:19.381 --> 1:51:20.715
craving knowledge,

1:51:20.799 --> 1:51:23.468
makes his way
to the Mage's Guild of Enclave,

1:51:23.551 --> 1:51:26.304
where he spends his days
in their vast library.

1:51:27.180 --> 1:51:30.934
-Though deeply devoted to his studies…
-Hey, buddy.

1:51:31.017 --> 1:51:33.353
…he still makes time
for the occasional adventure.

1:51:46.408 --> 1:51:47.659
As for Will the Wise,

1:51:47.742 --> 1:51:52.163
he travels far and long
to the bustling city of Vallaki.

1:51:53.039 --> 1:51:54.791
It's overwhelming at first.

1:51:55.333 --> 1:51:58.628
So very different
from the village where he spent his youth.

1:51:59.754 --> 1:52:02.006
But it isn't long
before he finds his place there.

1:52:02.090 --> 1:52:02.924
Hey!

1:52:03.007 --> 1:52:05.719
And with that, deep happiness

1:52:06.720 --> 1:52:07.971
and acceptance.

1:52:15.061 --> 1:52:18.273
And the storyteller? What about him?

1:52:21.317 --> 1:52:24.612
The storyteller keeps telling stories,

1:52:25.905 --> 1:52:27.615
stories inspired by his friends.

1:52:31.077 --> 1:52:32.704
One day, he hopes

1:52:32.787 --> 1:52:36.583
their tales of grand adventure
will spread far and wide across the land

1:52:37.459 --> 1:52:39.836
so all can know of their great bravery.

1:52:42.130 --> 1:52:45.467
But there is a story
that he can never tell.

1:52:47.427 --> 1:52:48.803
The story of the mage.

1:52:50.638 --> 1:52:52.682
Or at least not the real story.

1:52:54.350 --> 1:52:55.560
The real story?

1:52:59.272 --> 1:53:00.607
When she cast Sunbeam.

1:53:00.690 --> 1:53:01.858
Get off me!

1:53:04.152 --> 1:53:05.111
Goodbye, Mike.

1:53:06.946 --> 1:53:10.074
She expended the last of her energy,
and she vanished.

1:53:10.158 --> 1:53:11.910
El!

1:53:14.329 --> 1:53:16.998
But has anyone asked themselves
how she cast that spell?

1:53:18.833 --> 1:53:20.502
The suppression stone.

1:53:21.085 --> 1:53:22.879
She couldn't have used her magic.

1:53:26.591 --> 1:53:28.635
In the excitement, no one even noticed.

1:53:29.886 --> 1:53:31.930
But you see, the mage is very clever.

1:53:32.430 --> 1:53:34.682
A cleverness only matched by her sister,

1:53:34.766 --> 1:53:37.477
who, upon hearing the pleads
of the paladin,

1:53:38.394 --> 1:53:39.854
had a change of heart.

1:53:40.438 --> 1:53:41.815
Don't cry, Jane.

1:53:42.357 --> 1:53:43.650
My story…

1:53:44.317 --> 1:53:46.402
was always going to end here.

1:53:50.240 --> 1:53:51.783
But yours doesn't have to.

1:53:53.952 --> 1:53:56.621
Together, the sisters devised a plan,

1:53:57.121 --> 1:53:59.916
a plan to protect the mage
from the Order of the Black Hand,

1:53:59.999 --> 1:54:02.210
who remained hell-bent
on stealing her powers.

1:54:02.293 --> 1:54:05.713
So in order to trick them,
she had to make everyone,

1:54:05.797 --> 1:54:09.175
including her friends,
believe that she was dead.

1:54:09.926 --> 1:54:12.637
And so the sister cast a spell
from far away.

1:54:13.638 --> 1:54:15.932
Safe from the power
of the suppression stone.

1:54:16.015 --> 1:54:18.226
El! Do you see El?

1:54:20.603 --> 1:54:22.105
A spell of invisibility.

1:54:32.365 --> 1:54:35.994
Once the mage escaped,
the sister cast one final spell.

1:54:43.877 --> 1:54:46.379
The mage you saw die was not real.

1:54:48.006 --> 1:54:49.424
She was an illusion.

1:54:54.178 --> 1:54:55.430
Where did she go?

1:54:55.513 --> 1:54:56.639
No one knows.

1:54:57.974 --> 1:54:59.017
No one will ever know.

1:55:00.059 --> 1:55:05.899
But I'd… I'd like to imagine that she's
in a beautiful land, somewhere far away.

1:55:31.633 --> 1:55:34.052
She finds a small town to call home.

1:55:35.762 --> 1:55:38.306
Safe from the danger of the Black Hand.

1:55:40.183 --> 1:55:41.392
And it is here,

1:55:41.476 --> 1:55:42.727
at last,

1:55:43.853 --> 1:55:44.979
that she finds peace.

1:55:46.689 --> 1:55:48.650
That she finally finds happiness.

1:55:49.776 --> 1:55:52.070
And this is just a theory, right?

1:55:52.946 --> 1:55:54.280
How do we know it's true?

1:55:55.823 --> 1:55:56.783
We don't.

1:55:59.744 --> 1:56:01.037
Not for sure.

1:56:03.414 --> 1:56:05.500
But I choose to believe that it is.

1:56:07.085 --> 1:56:08.211
I believe.

1:56:10.463 --> 1:56:11.464
I believe.

1:56:13.925 --> 1:56:15.385
I believe.

1:56:16.803 --> 1:56:17.971
I believe.

1:56:19.389 --> 1:56:20.473
I believe.

1:56:25.061 --> 1:56:28.439
Guys! What's going on?
The lasagna's getting cold!

1:56:28.523 --> 1:56:31.734
Yeah, we… we just finished.
We'll be right up.

1:57:54.859 --> 1:57:57.403
-Holly, how do we play this game?
-Jesus, watch out!

1:57:57.487 --> 1:58:00.239
Jeez yourself!
You said you'd be done an hour ago!

1:58:00.323 --> 1:58:01.949
Look, it's our own little castle.

1:58:02.033 --> 1:58:04.952
I'll look in the manual
for like a starter campaign in here.

1:58:05.036 --> 1:58:06.412
Why do you get to be Dungeon Master?

1:58:06.496 --> 1:58:08.372
Because this was my idea,
and this is my house!

1:58:08.456 --> 1:58:10.208
You told me
this was not going to be nerdy!

1:58:10.291 --> 1:58:11.542
-This is super nerdy!
-Put him down!

1:58:11.626 --> 1:58:13.044
-Did you just fart?
-No.

1:58:13.711 --> 1:58:15.254
Something smells. I'm gonna puke.

1:58:15.338 --> 1:58:16.422
It's just old pizza.

1:58:16.506 --> 1:58:18.758
Old pizza doesn't smell like crusty ass!

1:58:18.841 --> 1:58:20.051
Blame it on the girls.

1:58:20.134 --> 1:58:22.970
Excuse me, girls don't fart.
If they do, it smells like roses.

1:58:23.054 --> 1:58:23.971
Listen to Holly!

1:58:24.055 --> 1:58:26.057
-You get these back when you focus!
-I can't see!

1:58:26.140 --> 1:58:28.684
Okay! You can be a halfling! A halfling!

1:58:28.768 --> 1:58:31.104
You want me to walk around like this
and fall over?

1:58:31.187 --> 1:58:33.773
No, you're sitting down and focusing!

1:58:33.856 --> 1:58:35.858
Give me my glasses back!

1:59:08.141 --> 1:59:09.767
I

1:59:11.352 --> 1:59:13.729
I wish you could swim

1:59:16.399 --> 1:59:18.484
Like the dolphins

1:59:20.027 --> 1:59:21.988
Like dolphins can swim

1:59:25.283 --> 1:59:27.326
Though nothing

1:59:27.410 --> 1:59:30.580
Nothing will keep us together

1:59:33.499 --> 1:59:39.672
We can beat them forever and ever

1:59:41.048 --> 1:59:43.926
Oh, we can be heroes

1:59:45.803 --> 1:59:47.680
Just for one day

2:00:08.201 --> 2:00:09.577
I

2:00:11.704 --> 2:00:13.664
I will be king

2:00:16.500 --> 2:00:18.419
And you

2:00:19.837 --> 2:00:22.173
You will be queen

2:00:25.176 --> 2:00:27.053
Though nothing

2:00:28.387 --> 2:00:30.932
Will drive them away

2:00:33.059 --> 2:00:35.186
We can be heroes

2:00:37.647 --> 2:00:39.482
Just for one day

2:00:42.193 --> 2:00:44.487
We can be us

2:00:45.655 --> 2:00:47.823
Just for one day

2:00:51.327 --> 2:00:52.745
I

2:00:54.538 --> 2:00:58.709
-I can remember
-I remember

2:00:59.835 --> 2:01:01.337
Standing

2:01:03.381 --> 2:01:07.176
-By the wall
-By the wall

2:01:08.010 --> 2:01:09.553
And the guns

2:01:12.014 --> 2:01:15.935
-Shot above our heads
-Over our heads

2:01:16.018 --> 2:01:17.770
And we kissed

2:01:19.438 --> 2:01:23.734
-As though nothing could fall
-Nothing could fall

2:01:24.986 --> 2:01:26.821
And the shame

2:01:29.198 --> 2:01:31.450
Was on the other side

2:01:33.411 --> 2:01:35.538
Oh, we can beat them

2:01:36.706 --> 2:01:39.875
Forever and ever

2:01:41.252 --> 2:01:44.547
Then we can be heroes

2:01:45.798 --> 2:01:47.675
Just for one day

2:01:54.348 --> 2:01:56.726
We can be heroes

2:02:02.815 --> 2:02:05.234
We can be heroes

2:02:11.324 --> 2:02:13.951
We can be heroes

2:02:15.536 --> 2:02:17.747
Just for one day
